(22, 257, 20, 'Policy, Innovation Systmes And Impact Assessment Program Leader-impact Assessment Economist', '2024', 'draft', '2024-12-11 12:02:19.749', '2024-12-11 12:02:19.749', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'sent', 'Je possde une grande flexibilit, ce qui me permet de m\'adapter facilement  mon environnement professionnel. Mon got pour l\'apprentissage m\'a permis d\'acqurir de nombreuses comptences depuis mon arrive chez AfricaRice. Par ailleurs, la bonne organisation, le travail d\'quipe et la rsolution de problmes sont des lments essentiels de mon efficacit, sur lesquels je continue de travailler pour m\'amliorer constamment.', 'Je matrise efficacement les outils d\'analyse et de collecte de donnes tels que Kobotoolbox, R, Stata, SPSS, et la suite Microsoft Office, ainsi que les outils de planification des activits. Je collabore harmonieusement avec mes collgues tout en faisant preuve d\'autonomie et de rsilience dans l\'accomplissement de mes missions.', 'Je m\'investis activement dans la ralisation des activits visant  atteindre les objectifs du projet RIZAO. Je porte un grand intrt  la qualit du travail accompli, en veillant  ce qu\'il soit bien excut, tout en respectant les valeurs de l\'entreprise et les directives de la hirarchie.', '\nJe fais preuve d\'initiative lorsqu\'il s\'agit de rsoudre des problmes, en adaptant mon degr d\'implication  mon niveau d\'intgration dans l\'entreprise et  mes responsabilits.', 'Je respecte ma hirarchie en excutant avec diligence les activits qui me sont confies. J\'adhre galement aux politiques de l\'entreprise et je valorise les contributions de mes collaborateurs ainsi que leur soutien.', NULL, 'Je fais preuve de flexibilit, d\'autonomie et d\'un fort esprit d\'apprentissage, ce qui me permet de m\'adapter rapidement et de matriser des outils de travail contemporains. Impliqu dans le projet RIZAO, je privilgie la qualit du travail, le respect des valeurs de l\'entreprise et une collaboration efficace avec mes collgues. Mes prises d\'initiative sont adaptes  mes responsabilits, et je m\'engage  respecter les politiques et la hirarchie de l\'organisation.'),
(23, 242, 145, 'Rice Value Chain Field Expert', '2024', 'draft', '2024-12-11 20:38:28.611', '2024-12-11 20:38:28.611', 'Several studies completed', 4, 'Yeo\'s contribution to social studies is acknowledged', 5, 'He shows commitment to the program objectives', 4, 'He takes initiatives', NULL, 'He follows instructions', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yeo\'s performance is generally good.', 4, 'sent', 'My interventions in 2024 as an expert in the inclusion of women and young people at AfricaRice should cover five countries, namely Cte d\'Ivoire, Nigeria, Burundi, Rwanda and the DRC. With the exception of Burundi, all my objectives have been implemented.\nMy key achievements include (1) Studies on the social barriers to the inclusion of women and young people in agricultural value chains in Cte d\'Ivoire, Rwanda and the DRC; (2) Workshops to strengthen gender-based agricultural innovation platforms (AIPs) in Cte d\'Ivoire, Rwanda and the DRC (128 participants from 71 organisations); (3) Agricultural entrepreneurship training in Nigeria, Cte d\'Ivoire, DRC and Rwanda (197 participants from 75 organisations); (4) Scaling up of at least 6 good agricultural practices/innovations in Cte d\'Ivoire, DRC and Rwanda; (5) Facilitation of 35 business linkages in Cte d\'Ivoire, DRC and Rwanda. These results are a prelude to my contribution to the overall performance of AfricaRice.', 'As an anthropologist specialising in social inclusion, I have a number of technical skills that AfricaRice could use, including: conducting (qualitative) social surveys and research into social inclusion in agricultural value chains; community mobilisation around initiatives; gender mainstreaming in the development of programmes; support for inclusive governance of agricultural organisations; capacity building for players in the agricultural sector, etc.  I also have skills in developing research and development projects. ', 'As a gender specialist at AfricaRice, during 2024 and under the guidance of my supervisor Dr Gaudiose and Dr Aminou (Policy Programme Lead) I coordinated various gender-sensitive research and development activities. NARS such as CNRA in Cte d\'Ivoire, NCRI in Nigeria, RAB in Rwanda and INERA in the DRC took part in the implementation of these activities within the framework of formal partnerships.\nMy interventions have also mainly covered the CGIAR initiative for the Transformation of Agri-Food Systems in West and Central Africa and several other initiatives such as Health4Diet, Excellence in Agronomy (EiA), the Initiative to Strengthen Sustainable Land Management and Climate Resilient Agri-Food Systems in Cte d\'Ivoire-LARACI; the Regional Rice Resilient Value Chain Development Programme in West Africa- REWARD and the CGIAR 2025_2030 Mega Programme.', 'Most of my achievements in 2024 are the result of personal initiatives, even if they remain under the supervision of my superiors. I note, however, that I must also work harder as a researcher to produce scientific articles, develop partnerships and raise funds by developing research and development projects. It should be noted that in my situation as a new recruit at AfricaRice, it was nevertheless difficult for me to take personal initiatives, given the lack of control over the resources to do so.  ', 'Since I was recruited by AfricaRice, I believe I have developed in strict compliance with the requirements of my employment contract. As a result, I remain quite concerned about administrative and ethical procedures. I also remain open to discussions about work and to understanding the challenges of my contribution to the development of R4D activities with agents, colleagues and hierarchical supervisors at AfricaRice. ', 'I think I\'ve shown leadership when it comes to managing my activities. However, given my lack of control over the budget allocated to my activities, I find it difficult to develop my own initiatives.  ', 'Overall, I think I have contributed to the achievement of most of my objectives. My strengths are as follows: coordinating social research (particularly qualitative) on the inclusion of women and young people in agricultural value chains; supervising activities aimed at strengthening gender-based agricultural innovation platforms; carrying out capacity-building activities for agricultural and rural stakeholders. Weaknesses to be overcome in the future are: Scientific publications; Stengthening my English language for my participation in CGIAR scientific forums and peer exchanges; And develop to the research and development projects for the institution.'),
