(79, 272, 149, 'Leader Rsd & Taat Coordinator', '2024', 'draft', '2025-01-14 08:13:53.221', '2025-01-14 08:13:53.221', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'sent', 'Efficiency in project coordination across seven countries has been demonstrated through strong support to the project coordinator, including the timely preparation of six quarterly reports (three for TAAT and three for TSF) and the TSF Project Completion Report (PCR) 2024. Seven TAAT II sub-agreements were signed, and the countrys implementation plans were closely monitored. Through coordination with the NARS partners over 40 climate-smart technologies have been adopted across TSF and TAAT countries, with tailored innovation packages addressing key challenges. Preparation and participation of three seed roadmap development meetings in Benin, Cte dIvoire, and Kenya offered a platform to showcase proven technologies and resulted the development of harmonized seed roadmaps. Capacity-building efforts have been carried out together with the focal persons in the target countries following a value chain approach, offering training on ESHS standards, value chain development, post-harvest.', 'Key staff competencies include expertise in identifying and mapping various rice technologies, such as climate-smart varieties, GEM parboilers, GAPs, and post-harvest management, in collaboration with focal persons for scaling and adoption. Proficiency in project planning has ensured effective implementation through well-structured work plans, budgets, procurement strategies, and timely KPI tracking for both NARS partners and AfricaRice. Capacity-building efforts have strengthened focal persons and value chain actors through training in value chain development for ASMEs, ESHS, task forces management, and technical reporting. Strong stakeholder engagement with project teams and actors has fostered collaboration across the rice value chain, improving implementation. Monitoring and evaluation efforts, including the development of a mini KPI dashboard, have ensured timely data collection, with 2024 data uploaded to MPRO for impact tracking. Support on MSIPs and resource mobilization REWARD', 'The staff\'s commitment is evident in the proactive approach to monitoring project activities, ensuring highquality timely reporting, and maintaining accountability from target countries. Engagement with diverse stakeholders, including private seed companies and national partners, underscores a strong dedication to collaboration and project success. This commitment extends to capacity building, knowledge dissemination and dissemination of innovations and technologies reinforcing long-term impact and sustainability. Strong focus on monitoring, evaluation, and knowledge sharing demonstrates a steadfast dedication to achieving project goals efficiently. There has been commendable commitment to creating synergy and collaboration amongst other AfricaRice projects and initiatives to showcasing and scaling of the proven technologies. ', 'The proactive approach to project implementation and problem-solving is demonstrated through the creation of a mini dashboard for KPI tracking, the initiation of monthly project meetings, and regular updates to the tracker. These efforts reflect a strong commitment to improving project performance, ensuring ongoing progress and ability to take initiatives. In addition, regular, deliberate communication with national partner focal persons acts as a catalyst for effective implementation, keeping the focus on achieving project goals. \n', 'Strong compliance with instructions and procedures is demonstrated through consistent adherence to project guidelines and timelines. The effective execution and coordination for both TSF and TAAT projects annual workplans, budgets and ESHS procedures ensure alignment with project goals and requirements. Timely submission of quarterly projects reports, integration of innovations into departmental projects, and continuous activity monitoring reflect a commitment to established procedures. Additionally, adherence to the staff code of conduct is evident in the performance of duties. ', 'Strong leadership skills are evident in the efficient management and coordination of project activities across multiple TSF and TAAT countries, ensuring tasks are completed effectively. Support Initiatives in driving innovation scalability within established MSIPs further highlights leadership. Additionally, leadership is demonstrated through capacity-building efforts, including training focal persons. A proactive approach to organizing meetings, monitoring progress, and fostering project team collaboration shows the ability to lead by example and steer the project toward its goals. ', 'TAAT II project is generally progressing on well. There is demonstrated strong performance in technical expertise, leadership, initiative, team management, and compliance with procedures. The ability to coordinate activities across countries, scale innovations, build stakeholder capacity, and ensure accountability shows commitment and effectiveness. Timely submission of highquality reports, integration of technologies, and stakeholder engagement highlight a proactive approach, driving the projects success. To maintain momentum, it is recommended to continue scaling \ninnovations and engaging stakeholders to meet targets by April 2025. Strengthening collaboration will enhance the adoption of climate-smart technologies, while expanding capacity-building efforts will ensure long-term impact. Focusing on quality data collection will lead to updated, accurate data in the MPRO system. \n');
