(170, 68, 150, 'Director Of Strategic Business Initiatives', '2024', 'sent', '2025-03-25 00:46:48.405', '2025-03-25 00:46:48.405', 'Francine is very efficient in her delivery and timely. ', 5, 'Francine has tre required skillsto perform her role. ', 4, 'Very commited. SHe had some down moments and picked up again very quickly', 4, 'Francine has a lot of ideas xhich she shares and implements. ', 5, 'Respects rules and procedures, while challenging status quo', 5, 'She manages the team very well and empowers them. ', 5, 'Francine has delivered an outstanding performance throughout 2024. She is highly engaging, professional, and diligent in all aspects of her work. She is a true asset to AfricaRice and a pillar within the Communications team.\n\nHer strategic lobbying at the CGIAR level has been particularly impactful, contributing significantly to the successful selection of AfricaRice to pilot the new CGIAR website structurean achievement that reflects both her vision and influence.\n\nFrancine\'s collaboration with scientists has been excellent, fostering strong relationships and enhancing the overall visibility and integration of communication efforts across teams. Her teamwork and leadership skills are commendable and greatly valued.\nI sincerely appreciate her achievements, dedication, and unwavering commitment to AfricaRice.', 5, 'sent', '5 Out of the 5 objectives were started and completed for the period. ', '100% tasks were completed with respect of the branding guideline and in alignment with client request. Beside they were all delivered in due time to serve during events. ', 'I remained committed to the shared vision and the collective work. I treated all requests the department received and I ensured the growth of my team.', 'The creation of a platform to support TAFS-WCA initiative was appreciated by the partners and program members. \nThe development of content and visual to rebrand the Abidjan office during the visit of the US Secretary of State enabled