(207, 230, 64, 'Head Of Accounting', '2024', 'sent', '2025-03-29 09:41:17.435', '2025-03-29 09:41:17.435', 'With the relocation to Mbe, Toure took up PV processing, he does this promptly. PV\'s that would take more than a week to prepare are now done within a few hours.', 4, 'The accountant understands well the entries to pass and immediately understands instructions', 4, 'Toure interacts well with colleagues and when given a new task he is unfamiliar with he will actively engage his colleagues', 3, 'The accountant stepped in to assist with PV processing when there was heavy workload in December, he is also ready to assist in fixed assets verification and tagging as well as reconciliation.', 4, 'The accountant follows the laid down procedures, he only raises PV after HQ approval and only prepares cheques after OCS approval', 3, 'The accountant has appropriately guided staff who come to finance office with enquiries, he also mentors the interns.', 3, 'Toure has brought efficiency in payment processing. Since December, he has improved turn around time in PV processing. This has made it possible to process payments within 1-2 business days. This is in addition with his current roles which he still undertakes diligently. He is also willing to join efforts in reconciling the fixed assets register.', 4, 'sent', 'J\'execute toutes les tches qui me sont confies avec efficacit, et tous les rappports sont soumis dans les dlais requis.', 'Titulaire d\'une Matrise en Sciences de gestion, ma formation academique cumule  mon experiece professionnelle me donnent toutes les competences tecchniques pour le poste ', 'Je m\'engage  toujours ateindre les objectifs qui me sont fixs.', 'Je prends au quotidien des initiatives dans mon travail', 'Je suis respevtueux des instructions et procedures.', NULL, 'Pour plus d\'efficacit dans mon travail, je souhaiterais beneficier d\'une formation dans certains modules en audit & contrle'),
(208, 166, 64, 'Head Of Accounting', '2024', 'sent', '2025-03-29 10:14:56.603', '2025-03-29 10:14:56.603', 'The coordinator prioritizes urgent roles and ensures the Outstations are running smoothly.', 4, 'The accountant understands her role well, she is able to identify transactions causing errors in the Balance Sheet and the SOA and corrects these immediately. She also provides guidance to both Outstation and HQ accountants on correct transactions to pass.', 4, 'The coordinator usually engages with the Outstations accountants in case some transactions are not clear or need corrections. Despite facing resistance from the Outstations, she has persisted in her efforts to ensure the Outstations are using OCS in all their processes.', 4, 'The coordinator has stepped in to assist PBU with month end closing procedures. ', 3, 'The coordinator provides guidance to Outstations on the proper procedures in financial processes.', 3, 'The coordinator provides guidance and mentorship to the junior colleagues on what entries to pass to correct identified errors.', 3, 'The Coordinator is technically competent and has taken up roles that go beyond her job description.  She has also stepped in to assist with the month end close and analysis of accounts.', 4, 'sent', 'Throughout the review period, I efficiently and timely executed my job responsibilities, leveraging available resources strategically. I maintained clear and consistent communication with Station Accountants, ensuring seamless collaboration. I meticulously reviewed month-end justifications, processed them in the system, and reconciled general ledger accounts with bank statements. This meticulous approach ensured data integrity, accuracy, and compliance with applicable rules, thereby strengthening internal controls at the station level. 5/5.', 'Throughout the review period, I effectively utilized my expertise, knowledge, and skills to successfully navigate and address tasks and challenges inherent in my role. Through collaborative efforts with colleagues, I fostered a dynamic and cooperative work environment, driving collective success and achievement of our shared goals. Rating 5/5.', 'I am wholeheartedly committed to the responsibilities assigned to me and consistently leveraging my full capabilities to contribute to the impactful work of AfricaRice.  I prioritize swift responses across various communication channels, including emails and telephone calls, underscoring my dedication to fostering proactive and efficient collaboration with both my supervisor and colleagues throughout the year under review.  Rating 5/5.', 'Over the course of the year, I have consistently displayed initiative in tackling challenges arising from my job duties. Utilizing my professional expertise, I address these issues independently with minimal supervision. Furthermore, I maintain effective communication by furnishing constructive feedback to my supervisor, contributing to a collaborative and solution-driven work atmosphere.  Rating 5/5.', 'Over the course of the entire year, I faithfully followed all given instructions, consistently adhering to the policies and procedures of the Center while executing assigned tasks in line with established protocols. My commitment extends to ensuring that each task is meticulously completed with the utmost attention to detail. This approach not only mirrors my dedication to upholding organizational standards but also emphasizes my commitment to delivering work of the highest quality and accuracy without compromising internal control.  Rating 5/5', 'Throughout the year, I have effectively mentored and supported Station accountants through regular coaching, guidance, and feedback, promoting a positive and productive work atmosphere.', 'I possess a strong technical foundation and have shown a commitment to teamwork and adaptability, taking on additional responsibilities to ensure team success. Rating 5/5.'),
(209, 60, 73, 'Sustainable Productivity Enhancement Program Leader- Crop Ecophysiologist', '2024', 'draft', '2025-03-29 13:10:33.690', '2025-03-29 13:10:33.690', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'sent', 'I have demonstrated a high level of efficiency, successfully completing and exceeding all five priority objectives set for 2024. I identified an optimal cropping system to enhance grain yield, labor productivity, and profitability using perennial rice varieties in irrigated lowlands of West Africa, which has been published. Additionally, I developed a participatory framework for prioritizing investments in climate-smart agriculture (CSA) innovations for rice-based systems, also published. I identified management strategies that reduce greenhouse gas emissions while improving rice yield, input use efficiency, and farmer income in rainfed lowlands, with findings currently under review. I published 10 papers, led the development of six concept notes and proposals, securing a total budget of $26.8 million for AfricaRice, and contributed to a $50 million concept note. I have also played a key role in scaling CSA innovations in Mali to reach over 200,000 farmers. ', 'I possess strong technical expertise in cropping system optimization, greenhouse gas mitigation, sustainable intensification, and machine learning, ensuring that my research translates into practical solutions for farmers. I have successfully led studies on perennial rice systems, low-emission management practices, and participatory investment frameworks, showcasing my ability to integrate agronomic, economic, and environmental perspectives in research. My technical proficiency is further demonstrated by a robust publication record, leadership in securing multi-million-dollar research funding, and expertise in designing and applying advanced analytical tools, including machine learning and climate change impact assessment. Moreover, my ability to engage with a diverse range of stakeholdersfrom policymakers to farmersensures that my technical expertise supports evidence-based decision-making and the widespread adoption of climate-smart agriculture (CSA) technologies across Africa.', 'I am deeply engaged in collaborative research, stakeholder consultations, and capacity-building initiatives, ensuring that my work remains relevant to farmers, policymakers, and development partners. My commitment is reflected in my leadership in multi-institutional projects and research proposals aimed at enhancing climate resilience and food security in Africa. One example includes the AICCRA project, which I lead in Mali and involves 7 CGIAR centers, one international University (Columbia University), and 7 national partners. Another example includes the MHRA project, which involves 3 CGIAR centers and 7 national partners. Besides, I co-supervised 10 Master students and two PhD. students in 2024, who all successfully graduated. ', 'I actively pursue new collaborations and partnerships, engage with development organizations and donors, and explore cutting-edge technologies such as machine learning, climate data downscaling, and impact assessment to enhance decision-making. In 2024, I established a partnership with UNCCD - G20 GLI, securing $100,000 in funding for a five-day training on lowland restoration. Additionally, I initiated collaboration with GIZ, leading to a $560,000 project focused on greenhouse gas emission mitigation in rice-based systems. My engagement with the McKnight Foundation resulted in a $121,223 project on agroecology. I also successfully maintained partnerships with the World Bank and Alliance Bioversity CIAT, securing an additional $1.6 million in funding for the AICCRA project for AfricaRice. Furthermore, I played an active role in collaboration with Alliance Bioversity CIAT and CGIAR SMO in developing a $50 million GCF concept note for Cte d\'Ivoire.', 'I adhere strictly to all policies, guidelines, and regulations established by AfricaRice.', 'I have demonstrated strong leadership by effectively managing multi-disciplinary teams and large-scale research initiatives aimed at enhancing climate resilience in rice-based systems. I lead a team of seven research assistants and seven technicians, ensuring the efficient execution of research activities, data collection, and field trials while fostering an environment of innovation and collaboration. My leadership extends to securing and managing multi-million-dollar research projects, including the AICCRA and MHRA projects, which involve multiple CGIAR centers, national institutions, and international partners. Additionally, my leadership in capacity building is reflected in the successful co-supervision of 10 Master\'s and two PhD students in 2024, all of whom graduated. My leadership achievements and research impact have led to my appointment as a co-lead of the Climate Action Science Program of One CGIAR.', 'Overall, I have demonstrated strong effectiveness and efficiency in exceeding all the priority objectives for 2024. I led impactful research that resulted in the identification of optimal cropping systems, the development of frameworks for prioritizing CSA innovations, and management strategies that reduced greenhouse gas reduction and increased rice yield. My technical capacity spans cropping system optimization, greenhouse gas mitigation, and sustainable intensification, backed by a solid publication record and leadership in multi-million-dollar research proposals. I am deeply engaged in collaborative research and capacity-building initiatives, successfully leading large-scale projects like AICCRA and MHRA, which involve diverse global partners. Through proactive collaboration, I secured funding for innovative projects that aim to reduce climate risks in rice production. My achievements have led to my appointment as a co-lead of the Climate Action Science Program of One CGIAR.'),
