(60, 'ok', '2024', 106, 150, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-07-11 10:35:21.781', '2024-07-11 10:35:21.781', NULL, 'ELECTIONS DU PERSONNEL', '- Organisation des lections du personnel ( vote, mise en place du bureau des IRP)\n', 'Mise  disposition des ', '2024-06-30', 'Effectivit du vote', 4, 'L\'objectif a pris beaucoup de temps sur plusieurs anne mais au final, il a vu le jour et le dispositif fonctionne bien. ', 'Objectif ralis depuis le mois de Juin  \nLes elections se sont tenues et les IRP sont en exercice', NULL, ''),
(61, 'ok', '2024', 106, 150, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-07-11 10:36:08.548', '2024-07-11 10:36:08.548', NULL, 'Standardisation des courriers administratifs', '- Mise  jour des contrats \n- Courriers', 'RAS', '2024-12-31', 'finalisation et effectivit des mise  jour', 3, 'L\'objectif n\'a pas t atteint dans les dlai mais je suis consciente de la masse de travail qu\'il y avait  finaliser. il faut mieux systmatiser les courriers. ', 'la standardisation des contrats a t effectu pour les diffrentes catgories  mais restent a finaliser les templates ( anglais/francais) et les mettre a disposition sur le sharepoint\nla standardisation des courriers ( lettre d\'extension) se fera sur l\'anne 2025\n', NULL, NULL),
(62, 'ok', '2024', 32, 73, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-07-11 10:55:13.168', '2024-07-11 10:55:13.168', NULL, '1. Identify High Yielding & Climate Resilient Rice', 'Phenotyping Oryza glaberrima mini core diversity panel and advanced breeding lines and selection of elite materials with high grain yield and superior tolerance to major abiotic stresses in West Africa. ', '- Availability and quality of test germplasm seeds. \n- Availability of resources i.e. budget and support staff.  ', '2024-12-31', '- Field, screenhouse and laboratory trials condcuted. \n- Elite lines with superior yield and stress tolerance identified. ', NULL, '', NULL, 'The Oryza glabberima mini core collection of 336 accessions along with 12 farmers preferred cultivars and advanced breeding lines were phenotyped and screened for adaptation anaerobic germination and submergence. The trials  were setup in a randomized complete block design with three replications with the objective to develop robust, precise and high throughput phenotyping protocols for rice germplasm and to map QTLs for gap traits through GWAS. The experimental data collection started in April 2024 and were in good progessed until September 2024. ', ''),
(63, 'ok', '2024', 139, 92, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-07-11 10:55:26.081', '2024-07-11 10:55:26.081', NULL, 'Architechture rseau Ndiaye', 'cartographie Schma du rseau avec les quipement ', 'plan dtaill des quipement avec leur emplacement rseau et mot de passe.\n', '2024-04-24', '10', 5, 'Le reseau a t bien cartographi et les quipement bien identifis et repertoris. La prise en main a t bien effectues. Et des propositions ont t faites.', 'l\'objectif a t atteint. Nous avons russi  avoir les accs de tous les quipements.', 'Larchitecture rseau de Ndiaye progresse bien : cblage refait, switches mis  jour, scurit renforce, et Wi-Fi install. Quelques ajustements restent  faire sur la couverture Wi-Fi et la documentation.', ''),
(64, 'ok', '2024', 32, 73, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-07-11 11:06:57.714', '2024-07-11 11:06:57.714', NULL, '2. Demonstrate & Scale-out Ajinomoto Fertilizer. ', 'Demonstrating and scaling Ajinomoto byproduct fertilizer management option for local rice with high market value in irrigated lowland ecologies at the Guinea Savannah and Forest agro-climatic zones in Cote dIvoire.', '- Availability of resources i.e. budget and support staff. \n- Weather and farmers fields conditions at the project sites. ', '2024-12-31', '- On-farm demonstration trials conducted in farmers fields. \n- Farmers trained and exposed to Ajinomoto fertilizer management. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ajinomoto by-product fertilizer management has been developed and demonstrated in farmers fields under irrigated lowland conditions in the three major rice production areas in Cote dIvoire. Thirty smallholder rice farmers (with 20% of women) were selected and trained to participate to the on-farm demonstration trials in two adjacent fields whereby one (Plot A) was fertilized with the extension recommended NPK and Urea doses and the other (Plot B) with Ajinomoto by-product in replacement of Urea at the N equivalent dose.  The trials were implemented from April to September 2024 and data collection and field visits were in good progress in the three locations.   ', ''),
(65, 'ok', '2024', 32, 73, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-07-11 11:17:12.809', '2024-07-11 11:17:12.809', NULL, '3. Evaluate Multiple Harvest System in Stage 1. ', 'Evaluating the regrowth capacity, development, and grain yield of stage 1 breeding lines and elite materials for multiple harvest rice system in irrigated lowland conditions at AfricaRice Mbe and Ndiaye stations. ', '- Availability of resources i.e. budget and support staff. \n- Availability and quality of test germplasm seeds. ', '2024-12-31', '- Field experimental trials conducted at Mbe and Ndiaye stations. \n- Stage 1 and breeding lines with good regrowth capacity identified. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Stage 1 breeding lines of 900+ entries were evaluated for their main crop harvest yields, regrowth and development and ratoon yields in irrigated lowland ecologies across AfricaRice stations in Cote d\'Ivoire, Senegal and Nigeria. The field trials were established from February 2024 and experienced some drought and cold stress which impacted the plants growth and development and reduced the grain yield of the main crop as compared to the ratoon crop depending on the location. Overall, the preliminary results are quite interesting with some breeding lines including inbreds and hybrids exhibiting good regrowth and ratooning capacity with grain yield ranging from 5 to 10 t/ha. ', ''),
(66, 'ok', '2024', 32, 73, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-07-11 11:56:27.007', '2024-07-11 11:56:27.007', NULL, '4. Implement Agric Drone Platform for Field Ops. ', 'Implementing agricultural drone platform for precision field operations and crop management for spraying herbicides, pesticides, and spreading fertilizer at AfricaRice Mbe research station. ', '- Availability of resources and logistics i.e. budget, support staff, coordination with TSA-Cote d\'Ivoire. \n- Good timing for the training in Abidjan & Bouake, and launching of the drones. ', '2024-12-31', '- Equipment, hardwares and softwares calibrated and setup. \n- Theorical and hands-on training of operating and maintenance delivered. \n- Field operations and crop management protocols developed. ', NULL, '', NULL, 'Two agricultural drones DJI AGRAS T20P have been purchased along with their batteries, accessoris and spare parts and one generator with TSA-CI in Abidjan and delivered at AfricaRice Bouake in June 2024. We have participated in a hands-on workshop including theorical and practical trainings on the drones operations and maintenance organized by TSA-CI in September 2024. With the technical support of TSA-CI engineers, we have setup, configured and calibrated the two drones and designed them for the different field operations i.e. one for spraying herbicides/pesticides and the other for spreading fertilizer in the field trials and seed production fields at AfricaRice M\'be station. ', ''),
