(156, 'ok', '2024', 80, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-02 08:56:13.701', '2024-08-02 08:56:13.701', NULL, 'Objective 1', 'Provide soil and plant analysis service to scientists and external partners with high quality control.\n', 'Availability of good quality chemical products in the lab in time.\n', '2024-12-31', 'Delivery of high-quality analytical in accordance with the parameters requested\n', 5, 'That is an excellent achievement. Over 5000 samples were analyzed for more than 10 parameters using high quality and effective methods. ', 'During current contract, 5161 samples of soils; plants; waters, fertilizer and biochars samples were analyzed by all the different methods of analysis at the laboratory. A special focus of quality control was put on the sample analyzes. 1387 rice grains were analyzed by the XRF method, 3773 soils, plants, fertilizers; waters; and biochars samples were analyzed by the conventional method. More than twenty (20) parameters were determined (pH (H2O); pH (Kcl); electrical conductivity; pF; organic carbon; texture; N-Total; P-total; P.Bray1; P.Olsen; moisture; dry matter; K-total; K-exchangeable; Na-exchangeable; Ca-exchangeable; Mg-exchangeable; CEC; Fe-total; Fe-exchangeable.....). \nThe scientists who have benefited from the soil laboratory service are Dr Dossou-Yovo Elliott; Dr Kalimuthu Senthilkumar; Dr Ali Ibrahim; Dr Ndindeng Sali Atanga; Dr Belko Nouhoun; Dr Yadav Shailesh; Dr Olivier Husson (CIRAD).\nWe continue to receive samples from NARS and other partners\n', '4165 samples of soils; plants; waters and fertilizer samples were analyzed by all the different methods of analysis From January 2024 to now. \nWe continue to receive samples for analysis from Ivory Coast; Nigeria; Senegal; Madagascar\n', ''),
