(175, 'ok', '2024', 217, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-05 16:25:26.178', '2024-08-05 16:25:26.178', NULL, 'Product evalauation & release', 'Testing, Trailing and Data-driven decisions of upland breeding pipeline by Establishing Stage 1, MET, OFT, NPT trails  With defined testing networks and SOPs.\n	Data collection, Data management, Combined analysis & Data-driven decisions with EBS unit of AfricaRice.\n	Sampling and Coordination for grain quality tests, HT genotyping, disease & pests screening.', NULL, '2024-12-31', '	Varietal release, quality seed production and linkage with seed scaling & seed systems research', 5, 'Outstanding trial hanling and working with genomics for parental selection.', '  1-Implemented the  2024 stage 1 yield trial(898 lines) in p-Rep design (20% repetition ) at three AR breeding stations in 2024. Agronomic data, disease, grain quality data as  well as the trial was genotyped with mid density 1 K Rica panel. Disease screening for blast and grain quality data was also captured from this trial.  GEBVs was estimated for parental recycling to establish  2025 crossing block in DELS_U pipeline.\n2-Through 2024 BTF, we had implemented upland MET( six countries: Cote di Ivoire, Mali, Sierra Leone, Nigeria, Guinea, Uganda and 7 locations)  late stage OFT(five countries:  Cote di Ivoire, Mali, Sierra Leone, Guinea, Chad in  total 150 farms )  and NPT( Cote di Ivoire, Mali, Sierra Leone,  Guinea). Data from these trails have been uploaded to EBS and combined analysis was performed  in MET & OFT trial.\n3-	In addition, the rainfed upland rice breeding pipeline(DELS_U)  has  piloted  on-farm  genomic selection (GS) in sparse testing design using stage 1 yield trial.', NULL, NULL),
(176, 'ok', '2024', 106, 150, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-05 16:30:41.728', '2024-08-05 16:30:41.728', NULL, 'Recrutement', 'suivi des activits de recrutement\ntransmission mensuelle des KPI au manageemnt', 'RAS', '2024-12-31', 'transmission effective des KPI', 5, 'Beaucoup d\'avancer au niveau du recrutement. Depuis qu\'on a pu recruter des consultants pour degrossir les nombre, ca va beaucoup mieux. Armande doit apprendre  remonter quand les choses n\'avancent pas, c\'est pas de la dlation mais cela permettra d\'avancer plus vite. ', 'le suiv du recrutement est toujours effectif.\npar contre la communication mensuelle des donnes n\'a pas t effective faute de temps  et d\'efficacit  oprationnelle', NULL, ''),
(177, 'ok', '2024', 200, 244, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-05 21:48:26.110', '2024-08-05 21:48:26.110', NULL, 'Field Trial management and Implementation', 'Establish, Manage, and organize field trials according to the provided protocols.\n Field lay out design and implementation of AYT (Advanced Yield Trials), OYT (Observation Yield Trials), and MET (Multi-Environment Trials) NPT (National Performance Trial) in the diverse ecological landscapes across Madagascar\n', '1. Field Layout Completion:  Design and implement field layouts for 100% of the planned AYT, OYT, MET, and NPT trials.   \r\n2. Protocol Adherence: Ensure all trials adhere strictly to the provided protocols without deviations.\r\n3. Timely Execution: Complete all field layout designs and implementations by the December 2024 deadline.\r\n4. Quality Assurance: Achieve compliance with quality standards for field layout designs, ensuring they meet the specified requirements and conditions of the diverse ecological landscapes.\r\n5. Documentation and Reporting: Maintain comprehensive documentation of the field layouts and implementation processes and provide detailed reports as required\r', '2024-12-31', 'Successfully design and implement field layouts for 100% of planned AYT, OYT, MET, and NPT across diverse ecological landscapes in Madagascar by December 2024, ensuring adherence to all provided protocols', 5, 'Excellent field book preparation and implementation.', 'In 2024, I successfully designed and implemented field layouts for 100% of AYT, OYT, MET, and NPT trials across diverse ecological landscapes in Madagascar, ensuring strict adherence to protocols. I effectively managed trial logistics, team coordination, and environmental challenges, ensuring timely execution. Despite resource constraints and site variability, I adapted layouts to different conditions and improved efficiency. ', 'The trials (AYT, OYT, MET, NPT) were implemented according to protocols in diverse ecological zones. The plots were well designed and installed. All planned data were accurately collected.', ''),
(178, 'ok', '2024', 200, 244, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-05 22:18:59.437', '2024-08-05 22:18:59.437', NULL, 'Efficient Data Collection and Analysis for Trials', 'Ensure prompt collection of relevant agronomic and post-harvest data for all trials.\r\nData collection using digital tools and encoding the data into the computer, keeping accuracy and consistency. Implement software data analytics (EBS or BMS) to perform preliminary statistical analysis, ensuring that the report aligns with the required standards. Ensure the data integrity and prepare preliminary statistical repo\rrt', '1. Timely Data Collection: Complete 100% of agronomic and post-harvest data collection and digital encoding for all trials within the specified timelines.\n2. Accuracy and Consistency: Maintain a data accuracy and consistency rate of 99% throughout the collection and encoding processes.\n3. Use of Software: Effectively utilize EBS or BMS software for preliminary statistical analysis of the data.\n4. Report Generation: Generate reports that meet all required standards and are ready by the December 2024 deadline.\n5. Data Integrity: Ensure the integrity of the data through rigorous validation checks and adherence to data management best practices.', '2024-12-31', 'Achieve 100% timely collection and digital encoding of agronomic and post-harvest data for all trials with 99% accuracy and consistency, utilizing EBS or BMS for preliminary statistical analysis, and generating reports that meet required standards by December 2024', 4, 'Great data collection but accuracy can be improved such as maturity date...', 'I ensured 100% timely collection and digital encoding of agronomic and post-harvest data for all trials, maintaining 99% accuracy and consistency. Using statistical tools, I conducted preliminary statistical analyses and generated reports that met required standards. Despite challenges such as field data variability and system limitations, I maintained high data quality through rigorous validation and team coordination. Moving forward, I plan to enhance automation and streamline data workflows for greater efficiency.', 'Relevant agronomic and post-harvest data were collected promptly using digital tools, ensuring accuracy and consistency. The data were successfully encoded and analyzed using BMS/EBS for preliminary statistical analysis. The integrity of the data was maintained, and reports met the required standards.', ''),
(179, 'ok', '2024', 200, 244, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-06 03:55:07.192', '2024-08-06 03:55:07.192', NULL, 'Digital management of Rice Germplasm, seed storage', 'Manage and organize rice germplasm and seed storage using barcodes and digital data base.\nClearly record trial entries by cropping seasons to streamline access and retrival for different trials. As well as regularly update the seed inventory to reflect new additions and usage, ensuring accurate records. Implement a digital barcode system to efficiently track and manage seed storage.', '1. Barcode System Implementation: Successfully implement a digital barcode system for 100% accurate tracking and management of rice germplasm and seed storage.\r\n2. Data Accuracy: Achieve 100% accuracy in tracking and managing rice germplasm and seed storage through the barcode system.\r\n3. Quarterly Updates: Provide accurate quarterly updates reflecting new additions and usage of seeds and germplasm.\r\n4. Clear Recording: Ensure all trial entries are clearly recorded by cropping seasons to facilitate efficient access and retrieval.\r\n5. Timely Completion: Complete all implementation, updates, and recording by the December 2024 deadline.\r', '2024-12-31', 'Implement a digital barcode system to achieve 100% accurate tracking and management of rice germplasm and seed storage, with quarterly updates reflecting new additions and usage, and ensure clear recording of trial entries by cropping seasons to streamline access and retrieval for different trials by December 2024.\r', 5, 'Excellent digitization of the trialing process.', 'In 2024, I successfully implemented a digital barcode system for tracking and managing rice germplasm and seed storage with 100% accuracy. I ensured quarterly updates reflecting new additions and usage while maintaining clear records of trial entries by cropping seasons. This improved efficiency, accessibility, and retrieval for different trials. Challenges included initial system setup and staff adaptation, which I addressed through training and process optimization. Moving forward, I aim to enhance automation and integrate real-time tracking for even greater efficiency.', 'The rice germplasm and seed storage were well organized with a digital database and barcode system. Trial entries were clearly recorded by cropping seasons, streamlining access and retrieval for different trials. The seed inventory was regularly updated to reflect new additions and usage, ensuring accurate records. The barcode system improved efficiency in tracking and managing seed storage, though initial technical setup delays slightly affected early implementation.', ''),
(180, 'ok', '2024', 200, 244, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-06 03:59:46.939', '2024-08-06 03:59:46.939', NULL, 'Seasonal and Annual Technical Reporting on Trials ', 'Writing seasonal and annual technical report on different trials including data analytics.\r\n\rOrganize the agronomic field data and produce reports that would contribute to write a scientific publication. Stay informed and apply recent innovations in data management to facilitate data transferability and enhance confidence in seed and data quality control and quality assurance.\r', '1. Report Production: Complete 100% of seasonal and annual technical reports on different trials, incorporating advanced data analytics, by the specified deadlines.\r\n2. Scientific Contribution: Ensure all reports are well-organized and contribute effectively to scientific publications.\r\n3. Innovations in Data Management: Apply at least two recent innovations in data management to enhance report quality and data transferability.\r\n4. Data Quality: Achieve 99% accuracy in data quality control and assurance throughout the report preparation process.\r\n5. Timely Submission: Meet all deadlines for report submission by December 2024.\r', '2024-12-31', 'Produce 100% of seasonal and annual technical reports on different trials, incorporating advanced data analytics, by the specified deadlines. Ensure all reports are organized to contribute to scientific publications, apply at least two recent innovations in data management, and achieve 99% accuracy in data quality control and assurance by December 2024.\r', 4, 'Great compilation of reports but need to be submitted ontime. Data quality should be checked for scientific publication. ', 'In 2024, I successfully produced 100% of seasonal and annual technical reports on different trials, meeting all deadlines and ensuring 99% accuracy in data quality control. I incorporated advanced data analytics and applied at least two recent innovations in data management, enhancing the efficiency and precision of report generation. These reports were structured to support scientific publications and future research. Challenges included managing large datasets and adapting to evolving analytical tools, which I addressed by refining data validation processes and improving workflow automation. Moving forward, I aim to further integrate AI-driven analytics and visualization tools for more insightful reporting.', 'Seasonal and annual technical reports were successfully prepared, integrating comprehensive data analytics from various trials. The reports were well-structured and contributed to drafting a scientific publication. Efforts were made to stay informed and apply recent innovations in data management, which improved data transferability and confidence in quality control.', ''),
(181, 'ok', '2024', 200, 244, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-06 04:02:15.000', '2024-08-06 04:02:15.000', NULL, 'Participation in project and Breeding activities', 'Participate in various project and breeding related activities as requried by my supervisors.\r\nTaking part in field days of demonstrations plot, seed production and actively participating in different events as required\r', '1. Full Participation: Achieve 100% attendance and active participation in all assigned project and breeding activities, demonstration plot field days, seed production events, and other required events.\r\n2. Supervisor Coordination: Ensure all participation aligns with the specifications and requirements set by supervisors.\r\n3. Timely Engagement: Participate in events and activities as scheduled throughout the year.\r\n4. Effective Contribution: Contribute effectively to each activity, demonstrating engagement and fulfilling assigned roles and responsibilities.\r', '2024-12-31', 'Achieve 100% participation in all assigned project and breeding activities, demonstration plot field days, seed production, and other required events as specified by supervisors throughout the year.', NULL, 'Great organizaiton of field days and exhibitions, partners motivation and animation.  ', 'I achieved 100% participation in all assigned project and breeding activities, including demonstration plot field days, seed production, and other required events as specified by my supervisors. My proactive approach in engaging with team members and stakeholders ensured effective communication and collaboration, fostering a productive work environment. Challenges included scheduling conflicts and resource constraints, which I managed through flexible planning and prioritization. ', 'Actively participated in all required activities, including field days for demonstration plots, seed production monitoring, and other project-related events. Supported supervisors by contributing to event organization and ensuring smooth execution of activities. Engagement in these events enhanced collaboration with stakeholders and strengthened project visibility. Minor challenges, such as last-minute schedule adjustments, were effectively managed.', ''),
(182, 'ok', '2024', 80, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-06 08:39:45.824', '2024-08-06 08:39:45.824', NULL, 'Objective 2', 'Implement field trials and data collection and high-quality data should be submitted within three months of data collection.\n', 'Have all the inputs ordered in time to set up the trials\n', '2024-12-31', 'Sharing of high-quality data within 3 months after the end of each trial\n', 4, 'That is an excellent achievement given that most of the data were shared with relevant scientists and the remaining data are being processed. This is a good record that needs to be sustained. ', 'Eleven (11) trials were set up and supervised during this contract period, four (04) in lowlands (Orgamin trial; Mincer trial; Zn_Biofortification trial season 1 and Zn_Biofortification trial season 2), one in Uplands (Long-term trial) and six on-farm (Orgamin trials). Some data has already been transmitted, while others are still being processed. ', 'Eleven (11) trials were set up and supervised, four (04) in lowlands (Orgamin trial; Mincer trial; Zn_Biofortification trial season 1 and Zn_Biofortification trial season 2), one in Uplands (Long-term trial) and six on-farm (Orgamin trials).', ''),
