(214, 'ok', '2024', 174, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-09 11:19:00.977', '2024-08-09 11:19:00.977', NULL, 'Storage organization, seed production follow up', 'Organize, Register, and store all germplasm in the storage. Follow up the seed production and certification process for different projects in different locations within Madagascar', '- Organize all old germplasm by cropping season and by trials before storing the new harvested.\n- Arrange the new harvested by trials and put in the storage.\n- Register all existing germplasm in the tablet or and computer\n- Give instructions for the seed production establishment and follow up until conditioning storage.\n- Help to facilitate the certification by collaboration with SOC people.', '2024-12-31', 'All germplasm in the storage will be separated by each season and by trials and also easy to find when needed.\nAll seed production are well managed and the seeds will be certified.', 5, 'Superb storage mangement and great seed registry protocol.', '', NULL, NULL),
(215, 'ok', '2024', 224, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-09 11:48:06.668', '2024-08-09 11:48:06.668', NULL, 'Line Testing Stage Trial', 'Conduct rigorous field testing of fixed breeding lines, carefully recording observations and performance data to evaluate the agronomic traits and potential of candidate varieties for further testing', 'Evaluate 100% of fixed breeding lines for all relevant traits during field trials', '2024-12-30', 'Percentage of fixed breeding lines evaluated for key agronomic traits (e.g., uniformity, disease resistance)', 4, 'Done good job in managing the upland LST trial and capttured all the equired data from this trial.', 'Successful evaluation of 4000 F5 Upland lines and selection of stable lines for further testing.', 'Seed cleaning and preparation for establishing the LST trial is in progress for all the breeding pipeline (Irrigated lowland, Rainfed lowland, rainfed upland and high elevation).', ''),
(216, 'ok', '2024', 174, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-09 13:02:05.942', '2024-08-09 13:02:05.942', NULL, 'Conducting field day on demo plots', 'Organize field day for demonstration plots on new released varieties in different locations within Madagascar.', '- Inform farmers around the demonstration plots about the importance of the field day. For example, obtaining new varieties adapted to their location.\n- Tell them for the specificity of each variety\n- Call them to visit the fields and choose the varieties they prefer', '2024-12-31', 'Some demonstration plots in different locations within Madagascar will be conducted field day. Some farmers in different sites participated on field day.', 5, 'Great animation during field days and effort in preparing the field for demonstration.', '', NULL, NULL),
(217, 'ok', '2024', 174, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-09 13:19:11.976', '2024-08-09 13:19:11.976', NULL, 'Technical reports and exhibitions participation', 'Organize data and organize technical reports and participate in different field days and exhibitions.', 'All data must be carefully checked and write a technical report for each trial established.\nParticipate on different AfricaRice exhibitions and on different field day organized.', '2024-12-31', 'Each trial established should be have technical report with data well organized.\nAnd we will participated in different fild day and exhibitions before end of December 2024', 4, 'Technical reports should be submitted ontime, immediately after the field work is completed for making decision for the next season trial.', '', NULL, NULL),
(218, 'ok', '2024', 117, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-12 08:44:03.810', '2024-08-12 08:44:03.810', NULL, 'Seed preparation for all direct seeding trials ', 'According to the randomization, prepare seed of direct seeding rice trials (OYT, AYT, MET and OFT)', '- Trials List \n- Trial protocols\n- Trials design layout ', '2024-12-31', 'Trials seed will be properly prepared according to design layout', 5, 'He has successfully done all the seed preparation task in 2024.', 'I successfully completed seed preparation for 2024 upland trials OYT, AYT, MET and OFT-GS ', 'I successfully completed the seed preparation of OYTs, AYTs, METs, and OFT-GS, contributed to upland direct seeded rice trials establishment at the plateau site at M\'Be station and trials management. ', ''),
(219, 'ok', '2024', 117, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-12 09:35:20.462', '2024-08-12 09:35:20.462', NULL, 'Field management and Agronomic data capturing ', 'Ensure the success of the 4 trials (3 AYT and 1 MET): apply fertilisers on time, prevent competition with weeds and collect data correctly according to protocol. ', '- Entry list and seeds\n- Daily labors\n- Protocol and design layout\n- Tablet for data collection', '2024-12-31', '-Trials well stablished and managed according to the SOP\n- Data collected acording to standard  evaluation system\n', 5, 'He  has done  very good job in  field and crop management for all the upland breeding trials conducted in 2024.', 'I successfully completed the agronomic data collection for the AYT and MET trials and submitted the data to my supervisor.', 'According to the description of the rice standard evaluation system (SES), I successfully collected agronomic and physiologic data of upland direct seeded rice AYTs and MET trials evaluated at M\'Be station. ', ''),
(220, 'ok', '2024', 175, 93, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-12 10:12:02.933', '2024-08-12 10:12:02.933', NULL, 'GAP demonstrations for lowland rice', 'Establish 21 rice GAP demonstrations for lowland in the main season and rice-fallow-legume and vegetables introduction in the central highland of Madagascar and in Comoros in the off-season.', NULL, '2024-12-31', '- Number of established GAP demo plots in Madagascar and Comoros\n- Number of Rice-Fallow-Legumes trials established \n- Quantification of the yield gain ', 4, 'OK. Agree with the achievements. ', 'In Madagascar, 19 GAP demonstrations for lowland rice were established during the main season, with yields averaging 34 t/ha, except for two fields affected by flooding. In the off-season, six demonstrations promoting rice-fallow-legume and vegetables were implemented to enhance crop and food diversification for rice-based households. About 10 vegetable species were tested, including introduction of chia seeds, nutritious amaranth, and African eggplant. \nIn Comoros, three GAP demonstrations and three diversification trials were established in February 2024. Rice yield data were collected and submitted by a NARIS technician, but vegetable yield data were unavailable due to heavy rains destroying the trials. Another three GAP demonstrations and three diversification trials were established in October 2024. These activities were delayed from June due to late submission of financial reports by NARIS, which postponed funding and implementation.\n', '', NULL),
(221, 'ok', '2024', 175, 93, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-12 10:22:14.500', '2024-08-12 10:22:14.500', NULL, 'Training on GAP practices for farmer', 'Train farmers on rice GAP practices through farmers field learning days both during the main season and the off-season in Madagascar and Comoros and prepare training materials such as GAP chart and cooking recipes to support the training session.', NULL, '2024-12-31', 'Number of trained farmers', 4, 'Ok. Good job done in Madagascar. I do understand the challenges in Comoros. Try your best in the next seascon', 'In Madagascar, farmers field day were organized in 16 sites where 1543 rice farmers were trained on the GAP technics. During off-season, 203 farmers sensitized and educated on the benefits of crop diversification and eating diversified food. GAP training materials, including GAP charts, were produced and distributed to farmers.    \nIn Comoros, organizing farmers field day and providing training on GAP packages during the first season was not possible due to the Cholera outbreak. These training sessions are now rescheduled for January. GAP charts also have been developed and printed and will be distributed to farmers during the upcoming training. \n', NULL, NULL),
(222, 'ok', '2024', 175, 93, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-12 10:23:02.025', '2024-08-12 10:23:02.025', NULL, 'P microdose trials', 'Conduct on-farm P microdose trials and complete harvest and data collection from 10 fields in the highlands by Mai 2024', NULL, '2024-12-31', '- Number of trials established\n- Data collection and analysis\n- Writing report \n- Presentaation of the results at FOFIFA simposium ', 5, 'Well done', '10 on-farm P microdose trials have been established in the central highland of Madagascar. Yield data were collected and analyzed, and the results have been presented on a poster. Additionally, 12 second-season trials are currently ongoing.\n', NULL, NULL),
(223, 'ok', '2024', 175, 93, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-12 10:23:45.541', '2024-08-12 10:23:45.541', NULL, 'EiA Agronomy and Mechanization, DEFIS project', 'Support Ferticombo experiment for EiA - Agronomy and product quality; machine land preparation and service provision in Morombe and Ambatondrazaka and DEFIS Project in Manakara.', NULL, '2024-12-31', '- Number of trials established under EiA initiative; Data collection and analysis\n- Number of beneficiaries of the mechanized land preparation service \n', 4, 'Ok Agree. Well done with the poster preparation. Need to work on the data and writing manuscripts', 'Two seasons of the Ferticombo and GxExM experiments for EiA  Agronomy have been completed. The piloting of the power tiller-based land preparation service provision model was followed up, with data collected and regularly checked. The results were presented on a poster during the COM.', NULL, NULL),
