(239, 'ok', '2024', 54, 68, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-15 23:17:23.573', '2024-08-15 23:17:23.573', NULL, 'Satisfy to all translation requests', 'Provide precise and culturally appropriate translations of documents, reports, and communications between English and French to support effective communication within the organization and with external stakeholders.', 'Documents translation are requested within appropriate working days and time.\nDeadline agreed are reasonable based on document size.\nRequester is available to reply to questions when needed.', '2024-12-30', 'Translation Accuracy Rate: Achieve 100% accuracy in translations.\nTurnaround Time: Complete all translation requests within the agreed timeframe.\nClient Satisfaction: Maintain a high level of satisfaction from internal clients.', NULL, '', 'Satisfied with the implementation progress towards the objective', 'Im very pleased with the progress Ive made in fulfilling this objective. The steps Ive taken so far have been effective, and I feel confident about continuing on this successful path. I am looking forward to keep the same pace.', ''),
(240, 'ok', '2024', 54, 68, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-15 23:17:38.263', '2024-08-15 23:17:38.263', NULL, 'Edit internal documents', 'Review and refine internal documents for clarity, coherence, grammar, and formatting to ensure high-quality and professional communications across the organization.', 'Documents edition are requested within appropriate working days and time.\nDeadline agreed are reasonable based on document size.\nRequester is available to reply to questions when needed.', '2024-12-30', 'Editing Accuracy Rate: Achieve highest level of accuracy in edited documents.\nTurnaround Time: Complete all editing requests within the agreed timeframe.', NULL, '', 'Satisfied with the implementation progress towards the objective', 'Im very pleased with the progress Ive made in fulfilling this objective. The steps Ive taken so far have been effective, and I feel confident about continuing on this successful path. I am looking forward to keep the same pace.', ''),
(241, 'ok', '2024', 54, 68, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-16 14:53:34.440', '2024-08-16 14:53:34.440', NULL, 'Identify and recruit competent interpreters', 'Support the Center by identifying, assessing, and recruiting skilled interpreters to facilitate accurate and effective communication during events, meetings, and other engagements.', 'Established framework agreements for identified interpreters.\nPayment of interpreters\' invoices within appropriate deadlines.\nGet notification for recruitment requests within appropriate timeframe.', '2024-12-30', 'Recruitment Efficiency: Successfully recruitment of needed interpreters within the specified timeframe.\nInterpreter Quality: Maintain a higher interpreter rating from event feedback.\n', NULL, '', 'Satisfied with the implementation progress towards the objective', 'Im very pleased with the progress Ive made in fulfilling this objective. The steps Ive taken so far have been effective, and I feel confident about continuing on this successful path. I am looking forward to keep the same pace.', ''),
(242, 'ok', '2024', 54, 68, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-08-16 15:00:49.491', '2024-08-16 15:00:49.491', NULL, 'Implement digital management best practices', 'Enhance the Center\'s online presence by adopting and implementing best practices in web and social media management, aligning with AfricaRice\'s communication strategy to boost engagement and reach.', 'Being informed, within appropriate timeframe, of  all Center\'s events/activities.\nParticipate, when possible, to all Center\'s key events/activities.', '2024-12-30', 'Engagement Rate: Achieve a good increase in engagement (likes, shares, comments) on social media.\nWebsite Traffic: Maintain an appropriate/increased traffic for the website (French & English).\nContent Consistency: Ensure highest consistency in brand messaging across all platforms.', NULL, '', 'Satisfied with the implementation progress towards the objective', 'Im very pleased with the progress Ive made in fulfilling this objective. The steps Ive taken so far have been effective, and I feel confident about continuing on this successful path. I am looking forward to keep the same pace.', ''),
(243, 'ok', '2024', 149, 48, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-18 09:44:12.443', '2024-08-18 09:44:12.443', NULL, 'Analyse rice germplasm for nutrient content', 'Within the framework of the objective, we will analyze some 1600 gerplasms started under the MAFF project and being continue under the HealthyDiets4Africa Project for physicochemical quality, mineral and phytate content. In addtion some market samples will also be anayzed for mycotoxin.', 'Availability of support staff\nContinous funding from EU funded HealthyDiets4Africa.\nNo breakdown of our key analytical intruments ', '2024-12-31', 'Database of germplasm analyzed is available. \n 4381 O. glaberrima, 557 O. sativa ssp. indica, 255 O. sativa ssp. japonica, 18 interspecific inbred and 8 O. sativa ssp. indica hybrid samples were analyzed for physicochemical and mineral properties.  Some Glaberrimas have physicochemical, sensory and nutritional properties suitable for immediate promotion in Africa. Others have important traits that can be used for rice germplasm improvement and value-added products.\nAnother 800 breeding lines are being analyzed for physicochemical, mineral and phytate content.', 4, 'The physicochemical and mineral properties of the existing germplasm in the genbank and the newly created one should be a routine task for the grain quality lab. ', 'This objective was met and a poster was created and is on display in the Grain Quality and Post-harvest lab', '', NULL),
(244, 'ok', '2024', 149, 48, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-18 09:52:50.114', '2024-08-18 09:52:50.114', NULL, 'Preliminary studies on rice crackers', 'Supervise the Identification of 10 crops whose extracts are suitable for the production of rice-based crackers with the purpose of enhancing its nutritional content and acceptability', 'Availability of support staff\nContinoued funding from the EU-HealthyDiets4Africa project.\nNo breakdown in our analytical equipment', '2024-12-31', 'Preliminary data on different rice crakers. \nNovel rice crackers have been developed. These rice products are produced from a combination of unpolished black rice (CB1) and extracts of some indigenous and underutilized plant species reported to be rich in essential micronutrients such as Fe and Zn (Hibiscus sabdariffa petals, Adansonia digitata fruit pulp, Moringa oleifera leaves, Cyperus esculentus nuts, Tamarindus indica pulp) (Tharanathan et al, 2006 ; Chadare et al, 2009 ; Abagoshu et al, 2016 ; Muthai et al, 2017 ; Stadlmayr et al, 2020). The nutritional content of the novel rice products include carbohydrate, protein, lipid, phytate and mineral as well as essential micronutrients (Fe and Zn). Crackers produced from other crops like soybeans, ginger, groundnuts, coconuts or fortified with SunActive Fe, SunActive Zn and SunActive Mg (TAIYO GmbH) were used as references. These crackers have been earmarked as snacks for school feeding programs. Crackers fortified with Moringa oleifera leave extract had highest Ca, Fe and Protein content and those fortified with Cyperus esculentus nuts extract had the higher Zn and P. The analysis of other crackers and nutrients are on-going.', NULL, '', 'We successfully developed the rice crackers and analyzed them for phsicochemical quality. A poster was created and is on display in the Grain Quality and Post-harvest Lab. In addition, the crackers have been selected by the HealthyDiets4Africa consortium for choice experiments in Cameroon and Cote d\'Ivoire. This study is led by CITA in collaboration with AfricaRice and Dchang University.', NULL, NULL),
(245, 'ok', '2024', 149, 48, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-18 10:15:04.886', '2024-08-18 10:15:04.886', NULL, 'PADFA and FADCI Project completion in Cote d\'Ivoir', 'Complete the provision of processing equipment (GEM parboiler, destoners, mills, drying surfaces, moisture meters, tarpaulin etcc.) to 19 parboiling groups in Cote d\'Ivoire.', 'PADFA and FADCI continue funding\nAvailability of support staff', '2024-12-31', 'PADFA and FADCI project completion reports', NULL, '', 'This projects have been successfully completed and final project reports submitted.', NULL, NULL),
(246, 'ok', '2024', 149, 48, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-08-18 10:20:13.702', '2024-08-18 10:20:13.702', NULL, 'Coordination of four projects', 'Coordination of TAAT 2, Seeds4Liberia, HealthyDiets4Africa and MEADEN-VIVA BENOUE Projects. Lead the implementation of project activities in countries through sub-agreements or direct action, report to donors as well as supervise staff on this projects.', 'Donors continue to fund the projects\nAvailability of support staff\nBetter working conditions', '2024-12-31', 'Signed sub-agreement on the different projects\nProject reports (Quarterly or Mid-term).\nFirst interim reported successfully submitted for HealthyDiets4Africa project.\nAll quarterly reports submitted for TAAT-2 and TSF projects.\nInception report submitted for Seeds4Liberia project.\nMEADEN-VIVA BENOUE project signed and officially started.\n\n', NULL, '', 'Sub-agreement signed for all projects contracted. Some have been amended as need be.\nProject reports (Quarterly or Mid-term).\nFirst interim reported successfully submitted for HealthyDiets4Africa project with a very favorable rating.\nAll quarterly reports submitted for TAAT-2 and TSF projects.\nInception report submitted for Seeds4Liberia project.\nMEADEN-VIVA BENOUE project signed and officially started.', NULL, NULL);
