(350, 'ok', '2024', 196, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-10-23 05:27:46.072', '2024-10-23 05:27:46.072', NULL, 'Set Up MHR Trials', 'Actively participate in the import and export processes of germplasm for Multiple Harvest Rice (MHR) trials. Set up these trials in suitable areas of Madagascar according to the specific conditions required for MHR practice. Also, participatein the surveys to gather baseline information necessary for the establishment and evaluation of the trials.', '1-Timely Completion of Germplasm Processes: Success is contingent upon completing the import and export processes for germplasm within the planned timelines, ensuring no delays hinder trial establishment.\n\n2-Strategic Location Selection: Establishing MHR trials in strategically selected locations that align with the specific agronomic conditions required for MHR practices is essential for achieving optimal results and maximizing yield potential.\n\n3-Thorough Baseline Data Gathering: Conducting comprehensive surveys to collect baseline information is critical; success depends on the accuracy and depth of the data gathered to inform trial evaluation and decision-making.\n\n4-High-Quality Data Standards: Ensuring the collected baseline data meets high standards of quality and completeness is vital; successful trials rely on robust data for effective analysis and reporting.\n\n5-Active Stakeholder Collaboration: Engaging and collaborating with a diverse range of stakeholders, including farmers and researchers, is essential for fostering a supportive environment; their feedback and involvement will enhance the relevance and impact of the trials.', '2024-12-31', 'Germplasm Import/Export Efficiency: Complete all import/export processes on schedule, ensuring compliance with regulations.\nTrial Establishment: Establish trials in at least [specific number] locations that meet MHR requirements for optimal growth.\nBaseline Data Collection: Execute surveys in all designated areas, ensuring data is collected thoroughly before trial initiation.\nData Quality and Completeness: Achieve a [specific percentage] completeness rate in the collected data to support accurate evaluation.\nStakeholder Engagement: Engage [specific number] stakeholders to gather feedback and foster collaboration, enhancing trial relevance.', 5, 'Excellent work and dedication with MHR project and taking it to the higher level.', '', NULL, NULL),
(351, 'ok', '2024', 196, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-10-23 05:29:08.395', '2024-10-23 05:29:08.395', NULL, 'Develop a manuscript for scientific Publication ', 'Write a research article on red rice based on recent research and innovations. In parallel, participate in fairs and demonstrations to promote Africarice and its activities in Madagascar, showcasing the organization\'s projects and research to the public and local partners.', '1-Access to Comprehensive Research Data: Successful completion of the research article requires access to up-to-date and relevant research data on red rice, including recent innovations and findings. This includes obtaining necessary field data, historical research, and any insights from ongoing studies to ensure the article is comprehensive and impactful.\n\n2-Strong Collaboration with Local Partners: Building effective partnerships with local agricultural organizations, universities, and stakeholders is essential for both the research article and promotional activities. Success is conditioned on establishing at least three collaborative relationships that facilitate knowledge exchange, resource sharing, and support during fairs and demonstrations.\n\n3-Effective Communication and Presentation Skills: The ability to communicate research findings clearly and engagingly is crucial for both writing the article and presenting at events. Success relies on developing and honing communication skills, ensuring that the information is accessible to diverse audiences, including farmers, researchers, and local partners.\n\n4-Adequate Funding and Resources: Securing sufficient funding and resources to support research activities and participation in fairs is vital. This includes financial support for travel, materials for presentations, and logistics for organizing demonstrations. Success is conditioned on obtaining budget approval and necessary resources by the start of the project.\n\n5-Measurable Impact Assessment Framework: Implementing a robust framework for measuring the impact of the research article and promotional activities is critical. This includes developing tools for assessing audience engagement, feedback, and citation rates. Success depends on establishing clear metrics and data collection methods to evaluate the effectiveness of outreach efforts within the first year.', '2024-12-31', 'Completion Rate of the Research Article:  Achieve 100% completion of the research article by [insert specific deadline, e.g., December 31, 2024], ensuring all sections are thoroughly reviewed and finalized.\n\nNumber of Fairs and Demonstrations Participated In:  Actively participate in at least 3 major events throughout the year, including at least one international event, to enhance visibility and outreach.\n\nAudience Engagement Metrics: Engage with a minimum of 200 attendees at each event, fostering meaningful interactions and collecting feedback to enhance future presentations.\n\nFeedback and Evaluation Scores: Obtain an average satisfaction score of at least 4 out of 5 in post-event surveys, indicating a high level of approval and interest in the presented materials.\n\nPublications and Citations: Achieve at least 10 citations within the first year of publication, demonstrating the research articles impact and relevance in the field of agricultural science and nutrition.', 3, 'Publications and flyer proparation for newly release varieties should be enhanced.', '', NULL, NULL),
