(393, 'ok', '2024', 239, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-11-20 10:33:32.088', '2024-11-20 10:33:32.088', NULL, 'Seed Multiplication', 'Seed increase for all parental lines', 'Achieve at least 90% of the planned seed yield for each parental line.', '2024-12-30', 'Quantity of seeds produced per parental line compared to the target yield.\n', 4, 'He has successfully produced the sufficient amount of seeds for all the parental lines.', 'One kilogram (1kg) of seeds were successfully produced for each parents and stored in the Upland breeding cold room ', 'Seeds for all parents have been nursed and transplanted.', ''),
(395, 'ok', '2024', 25, 76, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-11-20 15:17:37.097', '2024-11-20 15:17:37.097', NULL, 'Capacity building of various stakeholders on Seed ', 'Train  GHU staffs, NPPOs and Students', 'The stakeholders and GHU staffs must know  how important seed health in the Germplasm exchange.', '2024-12-31', 'At least key GHU staffs attend at least  to 3 workshops / trainings ; GHU received students from at least 1 university, at least GHU recive one visit of the NPPO a year.', NULL, '', 'Capacity building of various stakeholders on Seed health \nIn 2024, I spent one week at CIAT in Colombia attending a GHU workshop on seed health and germplasm exchange. In March 2024, I, participated in the establishment of AfRice-HEALTH Network in Abidjan to strengthen the diagnostic and surveillance capabilities for rice diseases in 19 African countries. From October 1-5, 2024, we hosted the MEMINADER team from Abidjan and the MAAIF team from Uganda at AfricaRice M\'b. The workshop aimed to enhance skills related to Rice Biosecurity Preparedness\n\nOthers: Equipments acquired including a lyophilizer, Optigene-Genie III, microscope, centrifuge, thermocycler (PCR machine but not full)\n', 'I had fruitful collaborations with IRD, Geves, and IRRI for protocol validation and training, including the validation of protocols for Aphelenchoides besseyi with GEVES and Xanthomonas oryzae with IRRI. I participated in the FAO technical cooperation program workshop on developing the seed industry in Cte d\'Ivoire, representing AfricaRice at Hotel TIAMA in Abidjan Plateau on March 13, 2024. Additionally, I developed the AfricaRice-GHU website to enhance visibility for our activities and have already contacted ICT for its hosting on the AfricaRice server.', ''),
(398, 'ok', '2024', 162, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-03 08:37:55.235', '2024-12-03 08:37:55.235', NULL, 'Quality Management Systems', 'Revise and update SOPs to align with international standards. Conduct regular audits, document findings, and implement a standardized workflow for genebank activities. Enhance asset management through barcoding and labeling. ', ' Complete 100% of targeted SOP updates and associated audits. \n\n Implement workflow improvements validated through performance metrics. \n\n Achieve full asset coverage for barcoding and labeling. ', '2024-12-31', ' Update 8 Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), perform audits, and complete documentation. \n\n Complete barcoding and labeling of at least 95% of assets. \n\n Streamline workflow across all genebank activities. ', 5, 'The updates to SOPs, including revisions and archiving on SharePoint, ensured alignment with international standards, enhancing operational transparency. Staff training on GGCE improved proficiency, while optimized workflows through standardized labeling templates streamlined processes. Additionally, barcoding improvements for all 65,074 inventories enhanced traceability and asset management, achieving significant operational improvements.', 'SOP Updates and Audits: Reviewed, revised, and archived all targeted Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) on SharePoint prior to the genebank review, aligning them with international standards.\nStaff Training: Successfully trained staff and technicians on the use of GGCE, enhancing operational proficiency.\nWorkflow Optimization: Configured and standardized labeling templates and designs within GGCE for all genebank activities, ensuring a streamlined workflow.\nAsset Management: Improved barcoding systems and configurations for 100% of the 65,074 inventories managed in the genebank, achieving nearly complete asset labeling coverage.\nThis objective has been effectively accomplished, with all deliverables met or exceeded. SOP revisions, staff training, and barcoding improvements have enhanced operational quality and asset traceability. The genebank is now better positioned to maintain compliance with international standards and ensure efficient management of its resources.', ' Reviewed and modified all SOPs before the genebank review.\n Formed staff and technicians on the use of GGCE.\n Archived and documented all SOPs on SharePoint.\n Configured labelling for all templates and designs 100% in GGCE across all genebank activities.\n Improved the barcoding configuration for all 65,074 inventories managed in the genebank.', ''),
(399, 'ok', '2024', 162, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-03 09:19:16.430', '2024-12-03 09:19:16.430', NULL, 'Acquisition and Distribution Management', 'Enhance acquisition and distribution processes by addressing material gaps, improving inventory tracking, and reducing delays. Automate key reporting processes and align distribution practices with international best practices. ', ' Successfully track 100% of acquired materials with GGCE. \n\n Meet the 10day reduction target for service delivery delays. \n\n Fully automate SMTA reporting processes. ', '2024-12-31', ' Conduct a comprehensive gap analysis for acquisition materials. \n\n Ensure 100% tracking of acquired materials in GGCE. \n\n Reduce internal frictions causing delays in service delivery by 10 days. \n\n Automate SMTA reporting and standardize distribution practices. ', 5, 'The revamping of acquisition management, with 768 accessions curated and accessioned, improved gap analysis and streamlined processes. Full tracking of acquired materials through GGCE ensured data accuracy. Engagement with over 24 users and processing 15 external requests improved service delivery. Automation of SMTA reporting aligned distribution with international standards.', 'Acquisition Management: Revamped, curated, and accessioned 768 acquisitions into the genebank from 2019 to 2024, including 374 from CIV, ensuring comprehensive gap analysis and improved acquisition processes.\nMaterial Tracking: Successfully tracked 100% of acquired materials using GGCE, meeting the objectives key performance indicator.\nService Delivery Improvements: Engaged with over 24 genebank users and processed 15 external requests through EasySMTA, streamlining service delivery and standardizing distribution practices.\nAutomation and Standardization: Enhanced automation of SMTA reporting processes and aligned distribution practices with international standards, though further validation is required to confirm the 10-day reduction in delays.\nThe objective was substantially met, with significant improvements in acquisition tracking, reporting automation, and distribution practices. Further monitoring and analytics may be needed to quantify the exact reduction in delays. ', ' Revamped, curated, and accessioned over 768 acquisitions in the genebank since 2019-2024.\n Curated and processed 374 acquisition from CIV.\n Engaged with over 24 genebank users on distribution.\n Processed 15 external requests through EasySMTA.', ''),
(400, 'ok', '2024', 162, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-03 09:27:22.756', '2024-12-03 09:27:22.756', NULL, 'Database management environment maintenance ', 'Transition from GRIN Global to GGCE, ensuring all system components are fully integrated and operational. Maintain a robust database management environment to support genebank activities. ', ' Complete the full migration to GGCE without data loss. \n\n Verify successful VPS server installation and optimization. \n\n Ensure seamless integration between Genesys, the RBCA website, and GGCE. \n\n Confirm system functionality through performance testing. ', '2024-12-31', ' Complete migration to GGCE and fully operationalize the platform. \n\n Install and optimize the VPS server for the AfricaRice Information System. \n\n Integrate Genesys, RBCA website, and GGCE platforms. \n\n Deploy SQL Server Management tools for enhanced database maintenance. ', 5, 'The successful migration from GRIN Global to GGCE ensured data integrity and seamless transition. VPS server installation optimized system performance, while full integration of Genesys, RBCA Website, and GGCE platforms streamlined data exchange. Rigorous testing confirmed the AfricaRice Information Systems full functionality, ensuring a robust and reliable database environment.', 'Migration to GGCE: Successfully completed the migration from GRIN Global to GGCE with 100% data integrity and no data loss, ensuring a seamless transition.\nVPS Server Installation: Installed and optimized VPS servers for the AfricaRice Information System, enhancing system reliability and performance.\nPlatform Integration: Achieved full integration of Genesys, RBCA Website, and GGCE platforms, ensuring streamlined data exchange and accessibility across systems.\nSystem Functionality: Verified the operational status of the AfricaRice Information System, ensuring its full functionality through rigorous performance testing.\nThis objective has been fully achieved, with all deliverables met and operational systems in place. The successful migration, integration, and optimization efforts ensure a robust and efficient database management environment. Continuous monitoring and periodic testing will further maintain system performance and reliability.', ' Fully Migrated to GGCE 100% without data loss\n Fully Installed VPS servers\n Fully integrated Genesys, RBCA Website & GGCE\n Fully operational and functional AfricaRice information system..........', ''),
(401, 'ok', '2024', 124, 76, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-03 10:14:31.081', '2024-12-03 10:14:31.081', NULL, 'Contribute to seed health testing, phytosanitation', 'Contribute to seed health testing, phytosanitation and quarantine management', 'after sampling\n- health test\n-bacterial and fungal purification\n-conservation\n', '2024-12-31', 'check that the seeds received comply with the country\'s biosafety requirements', NULL, '', 'Completed\nAll health tests have been carried out on all the acquisitions that arrived during the year.\nAll the tests were successfully completed.', 'Health tests have been carried out on the various acquisitions.\nIn addition to this we have carried out other tests such as the products in the PSA AND PDA environments with the Team, Full time, ANT FM 30P AND RB 99 TM; also, the same products were used to make grains, that is to say that we put the different products on the seeds\n', ''),
