(439, 'ok', '2024', 95, 11, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:15:04.116', '2024-12-04 12:15:04.116', NULL, 'Mise en place des essais du breeding', '4- Contribuer aux  activites de breeding au niveau des parcelles-a savoir preparatio de semences ,mise en place des essais, gestion des parcelles, collecte des donnees et aussi les activites post recolte.', 'Attribution et preparation des parcelles par \n la ferme structure en charge de ses operation', '2024-12-20', 'le nombre d essais mis en place\nle type de donnees collecte\nle nombre d essais battus vannes et conserves dans la chambre froide.', 4, 'Objective achieved with success and within reasonal timeframe.', 'Nous avons contribu  mettre en place les essais de Upland; lowland et Hybrid et nous avons collect les donnes agromorphologiques qui sont en cours d analyse', 'j ai participer  la mise en place des essais hybride et lowland durant les saisons sche et hivernale 2024.', 'Activities on-going as scheduled. Ensure that all planned activies with Mr. Ly are finalised before close of the year.'),
(440, 'ok', '2024', 39, 11, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:15:41.174', '2024-12-04 12:15:41.174', NULL, 'le gnotypage ', 'Contribuer  lchantillonnage des feuilles pour le gnotypage des activits breeding.', 'La disponibilits des plates, du materiel de d\'echantiollonnag et de coupe.\n-La disponibilit du four pour le sechage des chantillons.', '2024-12-20', '-Le nombre de lign genotyp.\n-La qualit des resultats du  gnotypage. ', 4, 'This activity was timely executed and very well coordinated. ', 'nous avons echantillonnes durant l annee 2024 :\n  1790 lignees des essais OYT uplandF et irrigue pour l unite breeding.\n 2931 F1 issus des differents croisements.', 'Nous avons echantillonne pour les  essais OYT upland, 895 lignees et pour les croisement  F1 ,1466 individus. \n', 'Activities on-going as planned. Ensure that all planned samples are shipped out on time. '),
(441, 'ok', '2024', 255, 76, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:46:26.520', '2024-12-04 12:46:26.520', NULL, 'Evaluation of breeding lines and accessions for di', 'Evaluation of breeding lines and accessions for disease resistance :\n 1- Pathogenicity of 13 isolates BLB\n2- Screening of Differential near isogenic lines IRBB with BLB\n3- Screening of 342 glaberrima minicore to BLB\n', '1-	Implementation and experimental design in a confined area, screen house \n2- Development of inoculation technique protocol to Assess the pathogenicity of Xoo species associated to bacterial leaf blight of rice\n3- Screening of new germplasm resistance, data collection and analysis\n ', '2024-12-31', '1-	Identifier the BLB isolates virulent\n2- Resistant varieties will be known to BLB \n', NULL, '', 'The pathogenicity test of 3 BLS was carried out, followed by the pathogenicity test of 13 BLB. 6 BLB were virulent. The most virulent BLB was then used to screen 14 of the 22 close isogenic lines IRBB and 281 of the 342 glaberrima minicore. 8 IRBB and 61 glaberrima minicore did not germinate. A few resistant varieties were identified.   ', 'Development of inoculation technique protocol to Assess the pathogenicity of Xoo species were performed on IR24 and IR64. The pathogenicity test of 3 BLS was carried out, followed by the pathogenicity test of 13 BLB . 6 BLB were virulent. The most virulent BLB was then used for screening.', ''),
(442, 'ok', '2024', 255, 76, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:52:15.402', '2024-12-04 12:52:15.402', NULL, 'Contribute to the improvement of blast resistance ', 'Contribute to the improvement of blast resistance in rice by developing populations using resistant glaberrima germplasm : Introgression of blast resistance gene into elite but susceptible varieties', '1-	Parents will be nursed and planted for the crosses\n2- Emasculation will be done at booting stage\n3- Pollination will be taking place in the pollination room\n4- Genotyping of F1s and BC1F1 to select crosses that will be successful \n', '2024-12-31', '1-	Generation of F1, BC1F1, BC2F1\n2-Genotyping of F1, BC1F1, BC2F1 by MAS\n', NULL, '', 'The progeny of Backcross 1 F1 (BC1F1) have been backcrossed with the recurrent parents and the resulting seeds have been harvested.  Backcross 2 F1 (BC2F1) was backcrossed with the recurrent parents and the resulting 28 BC2F1 seeds were harvested out of 40. The rest will be harvested over the coming days.', '295 samples were collected for F1 genotyping. In line with the objective, a total of 40 populations were generated by backcrossing (BC1F1) blast-resistant lines and a few susceptible but high-yielding varieties.  The Backcross 1 F1 (BC1F1) progeny were backcrossed with the recurrent parents, and the resulting seeds were harvested.', ''),
(443, 'ok', '2024', 255, 76, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:55:51.023', '2024-12-04 12:55:51.023', NULL, 'Contribute to the molecular diagnostics of pathoge', 'Contribute to the molecular diagnostics of pathogens, including seed-borne and seed-transmitted microbes : \n1-	Sample collection, isolation, purification, identification and conservation of bacteria pathogens\n2- Evaluation of PCR protocol for diagnostics species of seed-borne disease\n', '1-	Percentage of target pathogens covered by diagnostic tools\n2- Available of reagents for PCR diagnostics \n3- Number of novel pathogens identified through molecular approaches.\n\n', '2024-12-31', '1-	Identification of species of bacteria ( Sphingomonas spp, Pantoea, Xanthomonas oryzae, Xanthomonas oryzae oryzicola and Pseudomonas spp et..) \n2- Identification of different species of fungis ( Curvilaria, fusarium, Magnaporthe oryzae ect) \n', NULL, '', 'Study on 48 samples, 16 samples per batch (1, 2, 3) of the effects of long-term storage of rice seeds in hermetic storage bags (activities related to grain quality Unit) and conservation of 30 bacteria and 2 fungi.  Isolation and conservation of 7 bacteria from inspections in Senegal. Conservation of 110 bacteria from plant pathology lab. PCR diagnostics were not continued as reagents are currently being purchased for pathogen diagnostics.', 'Installation of a freeze-dryer and freeze-drying of 12 samples. 106 BBs were grown and 71 grew, then stored. PCR diagnostics were not continued as reagents are currently being purchased for pathogen diagnostics.', ''),
(444, 'ok', '2024', 255, 76, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-04 12:57:28.576', '2024-12-04 12:57:28.576', NULL, 'Contribute to data analysis through bioinformatics', 'Contribute to data analysis through biometrical and bioinformatic methodologies, along with the preparation of program reports : Data analysis and report writing\n', '-	Number of analyses completed (e.g., GWAS, phylogenetic studies, QTL mapping) \n-	Number of new bioinformatic pipelines, scripts, or workflows developed and statistical accuracy\n-	Frequency of reporting\n-	Gain more knowledge in bioinformatics and biometric \n\n', '2024-12-31', '-	Number of datasets processed using biometrical or bioinformatic tools\n-	Percentage of results validated through experimental or independent computational methods\n-	Number of program reports prepared and submitted on time.\n-	Training sessions or workshops on biometrical and bioinformatic methods\n', NULL, '', 'The reconstruction of 15 models for glaberrima resistance was carried out.  Analysis of nucleic acid sequence data was carried out using MEGA, DnaSP. Analysis of screening activity data (glaberrima and IRBB), GHU distribution, nitrogen/drought treatment and Ka/ks analysis of vpg /CP sequences were performed using Sankey and R. 6 phylogenetic trees were generated. and 10 R scripts were developed. To enable this objective to be achieved, a need for capacity building has been identified and met by a training course in bioinformatics organised by the International Certificate in Bioinformatics and Genomics (CIBiG) in September 2024. Regular progress reports are sent to the supervisor.', 'The reconstruction of 15 models for glaberrima resistance was carried out.  Nucleic acid sequence data was analyzed using MEGA . 3 phylogenetic trees were generated. In addition, to enable this objective to be achieved, a need for capacity building has been identified and will be met by Training on the implementation of a monitoring and decision support platform for vegetable diseases and pathogens using a VeggieMon tool in February 2024. Regular progress reports are sent to the supervisor.', ''),
(446, 'ok', '2024', 11, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-04 15:49:35.322', '2024-12-04 15:49:35.322', NULL, 'Pre-breeding', 'To implement trait development and deployment strategies for rice under ABI-WP4 (DISCOVER) and PO3 of the AGGRi-2 Project.', '1. Trait audit framework that prioritizes traits for the breeding program based on estimates of return on investment and likelihood of success is documented. 2. Lines that combine target traits and majority of recipient background advanced based on MAS. ', '2024-12-31', 'Trait prioritization framework established by Dec 31, 2024. 2. Deployment and trait development activities carried out according to QC criteria in the trait development pipeline by Dec 31, 2024.', 5, 'Great work on Trait audit is completed to all breeding pipelines. ', 'Objective successfully achieved. Trait prioritization framework completed and accessible via GDI shared folder. BC1F1 seeds harvested for aroma, balst and RYMV deployments.', 'Trait mapping and prioritization based on all 9 target product profiles have been completed. Elite breeding lines from all 4 ecologies have been assemebled and crosses initiated for blast, RYMV and aroma. ', ''),
(447, 'ok', '2024', 99, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-05 13:46:19.091', '2024-12-05 13:46:19.091', NULL, 'Seed Authentication, Cleaning, Sorting, and Data ', 'Handle seed authentication cleaning and sorting of at least 3188 regenerated and 1800 characterized accessions using the Zig zag aspirator as well the lot of 500 accessions to be regenerated in the screen house and record the information in GG CE database', '	100% of the 3,188 accessions for regeneration have germinated and harvested and harvest bags are labeled without any errors or mislabeling. \n	Casual workers are recruited when needed \n\n', '2024-12-31', '	Achieve 100% accuracy in verifying the identity of at least 3,188 regenerated and 1800 characterized accessions including 600 constituting the Oryza sativa mini collection.\n	 100% of the 500 accessions regenerated in the screen house registered.\n	Successfully clean and sort 100% of the seeds from the 3,188 regenerated accessions. and 1800 characterized accessions\n	Enter 100% of the information for all accessions into the GGCE database with zero errors or omissions\n	Complete the authentication, cleaning, sorting, and data entry tasks for all accessions within the established deadlines.\n', 5, 'We would like to express our sincere appreciation to Mr. Yao Boris for his outstanding dedication and hard work. Thanks to his meticulous efforts, the payroll of casual workers has been consistently reviewed and verified every two weeks, ensuring accurate and timely compensation for all.', 'All targeted objectives for the year were successfully achieved with a high standard of accuracy and efficiency. The identity of 1,800 characterized accessionsincluding the 600 that form the Oryza sativa minicore collectionwas verified with 100% accuracy. \n\nSeed cleaning and sorting were successfully completed for all 1,800 characterized accessions. Furthermore, all relevant information was accurately entered into the GGCE database with zero errors or omissions. These tasks were completed fully within the established deadlines, reflecting strong commitment to quality, data integrity, and timely execution.', 'By mid-year, significant progress has been made in seed management operations. Authentication, cleaning, and sorting activities were conducted for all harvested accessions  using the Zig Zag aspirator.  All related information has been systematically recorded in the GG-CE database, ensuring proper traceability and documentation.', 'We would like to express our sincere appreciation to Mr. Yao Boris for his outstanding dedication and hard work. Thanks to his meticulous efforts, the payroll of casual workers has been consistently reviewed and verified every two weeks, ensuring accurate and timely compensation for all.'),
(448, 'ok', '2024', 99, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-05 13:46:27.767', '2024-12-05 13:46:27.767', NULL, 'Laboratory Maintenance and Equipment Upkeep ', 'Maintain clean the seed cleaning laboratory and document the evidence\nMaintain good condition equipment in seed cleaning laboratory: Zig-Zag Aspirator, Air purifier, scanner, scales and document the evidence\n', '	100% of the equipment operates without any breakdowns.\n	The operations department responds quickly when necessary if there is a problem.\n', '2024-12-31', '	Ensure the seed cleaning laboratory is cleaned and maintained 100% of the time, with weekly documented cleaning schedules and photographic evidence.\n	Maintain 95% operational efficiency of all equipment (Zig-Zag Aspirator, air purifier, scanner, scales) with minimal downtime.\n	100% of the equipment is calibrated precisely according to the instruction sheets, ensuring accurate functionality \n', 5, 'Boris maintained the seed cleaning laboratory in an exceptionally clean and organized condition throughout the year, with weekly cleaning well documented. He ensured over 95% equipment efficiency and achieved 100% calibration compliance for all key equipment, guaranteeing precision and uninterrupted seed processing operations.', 'The seed cleaning laboratory was consistently maintained in a clean and organized state throughout the year, with weekly cleaning schedules thoroughly documented and supported by photographic evidence. Equipment performance was sustained at over 95% operational efficiency, with minimal downtime, ensuring uninterrupted workflow.\n\nAdditionally, 100% of the equipmentincluding the Zig-Zag aspirator, air purifier, scanner, and scaleswas calibrated with precision, strictly following the instruction sheets. This ensured optimal performance and accurate results in all seed processing activities.', 'The seed cleaning laboratory has been regularly maintained and kept in clean condition to ensure a safe and efficient working environment. All maintenance activities have been documented as evidence of compliance with quality standards. Additionally, key equipmentincluding the Zig-Zag aspirator, air purifier, scanner, and scaleshas been kept in good working condition through routine checks and servicing. Maintenance logs have been updated accordingly to ensure traceability and operational readiness.', 'We would like to express our sincere appreciation to Mr. Yao Boris for his outstanding dedication and hard work. Thanks to his meticulous efforts, the payroll of casual workers has been consistently reviewed and verified every two weeks, ensuring accurate and timely compensation for all.'),
