(516, 'ok', '2024', 214, 135, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-10 16:05:53.244', '2024-12-10 16:05:53.244', NULL, '1.	ASSISTING IN DGS MISSIONS BY PROVIDING NECESSA', '\nProviding administrative support for DG and Vips travels during Science Week. (Travel requisition, subsequent justification in OCS and calcul of perdiem.\n', '\nRescheduling ICI Forum - Dubai, 2-3 July.\nDefining the operational model that underlies ICI and its definitions.\nWorking on the three priority business cases (IA/EA/EBC) and discussing the risk management/internal control framework.\n6th KAFACI General Assembly from 27-28 August Jointly organized by KAFACI and KALRO.\nAim: To facilitate the transfer of agricultural technologies and foster strategic partnerships for development.\nWAFI CGIAR High-Level Dialogue in China and Travel to Sanya Clonal Rice Program National Lab\'s Office (BMGF).\n\nObjective success conditions\n-	Sending mail to organizers to request logistic note, hotel reservation etc\n-	Assisting with booking of air ticket \n-	Assist with visa processing\n-	Calcul of perdiem \n-	Assisting for hotel reservation in Bouake\n-	Requesting a vehicle for transportation from Abidjan-bouake-Abidjan. Pick up and drop off from the hotel to the Airport. And vice versa.\n-	Putting in OCS the justifications of travel expenses made during the trip or mission.\n', '2024-12-20', '\n	Efficiency\n	Following instructions and procedures\n', 3, 'She has leanrt quickly but needs to improve on organizations of my travels and arrangements around them', '', NULL, NULL),
(517, 'ok', '2024', 242, 145, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 08:45:22.967', '2024-12-11 08:45:22.967', NULL, 'To deepen gender research', 'To continue gender research in the countries targeted by TAFS-WCA in order to gain a better understanding of the inequalities faced by women and young people in agricultural value chains', '', '2024-12-31', '1. Conducting studies on the challenges/social barriers of including women and young people in agricultural value chains ;\n\n2. Publish at least one article.', 4, 'Yeo completed and reported on the task', 'During 2024, I was generally able to achieve satisfactory results in terms of gender research. \n\nIn Cte d\'Ivoire, Rwanda and the DRC, I was able to collect data on the social challenges/barriers faced by women and young people in agricultural value chains, in particular. Apart from the study report on Rwanda, which is currently being finalised, all the other reports have been completed.\n\nAs far as publications are concerned, I have not yet been able to submit an article. I do, however, have four publication projects in progress, 3 of which have already been drafted and are in the process of being finalised. \n \nIt should be added that I was able to use data from surveys carried out in 2023 in Ghana, Cte d\'Ivoire and Nigeria to create an index on the perception of the empowerment of stakeholders in agricultural value chains.   This index measures the empowerment gap by gender and class. It will be the subject of a specific analysis.', NULL, NULL);
