(535, 'ok', '2024', 242, 145, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 11:02:29.718', '2024-12-11 11:02:29.718', NULL, 'Contribute to AfricaRice\'s development activities', 'Support gender mainstreaming within TAFS-WCA, other initiatives or activities implemented by the CGIAR or AfricaRice or if requested.', NULL, '2024-12-31', '1. Implementation of activities under Work Package 4 (empowering women and young people) of the TAFS-WCA initiative;\n\n2. Support for the development of initiatives or programmes in which AfricaRice and the CGIAR are associated;\n\n3. Participation in AfricaRice and CGIAR scientific or development events and activities.  ', 4, 'Contribution to the AfricaRice strategy acknwoledged', 'As a gender specialist, I was involved in achieving AfricaRice\'s development goals in 2024.\n\nIn the TAFS-WCA initiative where AfricaRice had the leadership on Work Package 4, I coordinated gender studies, workshops to strengthen inclusive governance of innovation platforms and the capacities of women/youth stroke in Cte d\'Ivoire, Nigeria, Rwanda and DRC. These achievements required the development of a partnership with the CNRA in Cte d\'Ivoire, NCRI in Nigeria, RAB in Rwanda and INERA in DRC.\n\nI have also contributed to the development of the following programs: (i) the Initiative for the Enhancing Sustainable Land Management and Climate-Resilient Agri-Food Systems in Cte dIvoire (LARACI-GCF); (ii) the Regional Program for the Development of Resilient Rice Value Chains in West Africa (REWARD-BAD); (3) and the CGIAR Mega Program 2025_2030.\n\nIn addition, I participated in several scientific events or other development activities of AfricaRice (meeting, workshop, CGIAR forum, etc.).', NULL, NULL),
(536, 'ok', '2024', 109, 41, 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', '2024-12-11 11:39:22.999', '2024-12-11 11:39:22.999', NULL, 'SUPERVISION DES ACTIVITES DU MAGASIN', 'Veuiller  la disponibilit des pices de rechange des engins', 'Avoir le matriel demand disponible sur place\nAvoir un magasinier qui fait le point du stock chaque semaine.', '2024-12-16', 'Connaitre les besoins des pices et lubrifiants\nVeuiller  la bonne gestion du stock disponible', 3, 'Correcte dans l\'esembe mais on doit pouvoir etablir des niveaux d\'alerte pour la mise en place des commandes ', '', '', 'La supervision des livraison et distributions de lubrifiant et graisse pour les vehicules se passe correctement '),
(537, 'ok', '2024', 101, 11, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 11:45:00.277', '2024-12-11 11:45:00.277', NULL, '4.	GDI Reports.', 'Follow up, collect, and consolidate reports from Scientists of GDI in 2024.', '	Standardized templates for scientists to use for reporting.\n	Pre-agreed timelines for report submissions.\n	Tools to monitor submission progress and send reminders.\n', '2024-12-31', '	Percentage of reports received on or before the agreed submission deadlines.\n	Number of consolidated reports delivered accurately and on time as per the reporting schedule.\n', NULL, '', 'J\'ai parfaitement consolid les rapports d\'activit mensuels de divers chercheurs du GDI et les ai soumis dans les dlais au responsable du programme,  la DRI et enfin au DG.', NULL, NULL),
(540, 'ok', '2024', 229, 20, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 15:12:29.157', '2024-12-11 15:12:29.157', NULL, 'Draft a collection of good practices', 'Identify and document good practices to be disseminated later to countries in need of appropriate anti-malnutrition interventions.', '- An accurate design of a research protocol, data collection tools, and desk research.\n- Timely feedback from the national respondents\n- Availability of good practices in the African context.\n', '2024-06-30', 'A published collection of good practices', NULL, '', 'This objective was achieved 100%. It therefore went through time and data constraints, mainly due to insufficient feedback from respondents. The data was supplemented by extensive desk research, which, with the support of the Steering Committee, helped to finalize the report and to meet the deadline of 30 June 2024.', NULL, NULL),
(541, 'ok', '2024', 229, 20, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 15:14:37.104', '2024-12-11 15:14:37.104', NULL, 'Hold  a consultation and reporting workshop', '- Present the results of the gap analysis report and the collection of good practices  to the national government representatives;\n- Consolidate these two documents with engaging feedback;\n- Establish a network to support exchange and technical assistance to governments to promote policy change.  ', '- Publication of the interim report on the gap analysis, and the collection of good practices.\n- Availability of time and financial resources;\n- Availability of the national stakeholders.', '2024-12-31', 'An available report on the regional consultation and reporting workshop on the policy gap analysis and tracker, and good practices collection.', NULL, '', 'This objective has been achieved by around 90% and is still under consideration.\nThe workshop was scheduled for 3 to 5 December 2024, after two postponements in October and November 2024. \nCurrently, the planning of related activities has been proposed, with (i) the terms of reference, (ii) budget, (iii) invitation letters to national government representatives, (iv) contact list, (v) translated versions of the reports, and (vi) an agenda. \nHowever, the Director of CERFAM suggested that the workshop be postponed to a later date due to other workshops being organized by CERFAM at the same time slot.', NULL, NULL),
(542, 'ok', '2024', 229, 20, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 15:21:33.676', '2024-12-11 15:21:33.676', NULL, 'Report on the HD4A project progress', 'Report on the periodic progress of the project to the EU following the Grant terms', '- Regular follow-up of the performed tasks\n- Availability of justificative documents', '2024-06-30', 'Submit Financial and Technical Reports from January 2023 to 30 June 2024', NULL, '', 'The periodic report and the financial report were all 100% achieved and on time.\nBased on the work plan for 2023 and 2024, the achieved results (deliverables) and expenses were reported according to the EU formats, and under the review of the HD4A project manager.', NULL, NULL),
(543, 'ok', '2024', 229, 20, 'draft', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-11 15:26:09.199', '2024-12-11 15:26:09.199', NULL, 'Implement policy and communication strategy', 'Propose short messages, events, and content on healthy diets and nutrition for publication on social media', '- Contributions from the consortium members\n- Budget to roll out events\n- Identification of institutional communication opportunities around the project', '2024-12-31', 'The visibility of the HD4A project to the public', NULL, '', 'This objective is an ongoing process. At this point, it can be estimated to have reached 95% in terms of regularity of posts on LinkedIn, X, and Facebook. Regular content is provided to the CERFAM Communication team, which is in charge of the dissemination proceedings. \nSuggestions to produce capsules and audio content have been made for YouTube but are still under consideration.', NULL, NULL),
(548, 'ok', '2024', 76, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 04:37:43.787', '2024-12-12 04:37:43.787', NULL, 'Pathogen diagnostic and surveillance', 'Develop and improve pathogen diagnostic and surveillance methods for rice pathogens while improving knowledge of pathogen genetics and pathogenicity; and fostering collaboration among pathologists in these areas. ', '- Our significant achievements encompass the formation of the AfRice-HEALTH Network, aimed at enhancing diagnostic and surveillance efforts in collaborationwith 19 SSAcountries\n- We were able to develop protocols for direct sequencing of pathogens from field leaf samples to facilitate rapid blast race identification and the identification of susceptible varieties\n- We detected pathogens causing emerging diseases and traced their evolutionary origins, including Bakanae, bacterial leaf streak, Pseudomonads and Pantoea, as well as re-emerging bacterial blight (BLB) in areas where they had not previously been identified\n- Additionally, we enhanced the pathogen isolate bank at AfricaRice with carefully collected and preserved isolates\n- Facilities for plant pathology research at AfricaRice were established and refurbished, which included replacing outdated equipment in the laboratories, constructing a growth chamber, screenhouses, and disease screening fields\n- We also built capacity of our staff, students and various stakeholders, and established strong collaborations', '2024-12-12', '- Develop and strengthen networks of plant health practitioners to diagnose, monitor, and manage rice diseases\n- Maitain a collaction of reference strains\n- Support national programs with diagnosis of new pathogen strains by improving their capacity', 5, 'Great initiative in establishing the AfRice-HEALTH Network, try to link it with the AWBTF network.', '', NULL, NULL),
(551, 'ok', '2024', 76, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 05:29:24.094', '2024-12-12 05:29:24.094', NULL, 'Identify sources of disease resistance', 'This objective involves screening of both newly developed and existing rice breeding lines/accessions/ differentials to identify disease-resistant genotypes, as well as those that are susceptible for potential replacement; it also includes the identification of new sources of disease resistance and the associated genes, and develop efficient techniques for screening rice germplasm for disease resistance', 'We have successfully maintained a set of differentials for key diseases and used these differential lines to identify blast and bacterial blight resistance genes that have been recommended to breeders. A cumulative screening of nearly 8000 breeding lines and accessions has been accomplished, with the results shared with breeders and NARs partners. Multiple sources of resistance have been identified, with a few characterized to uncover the genetic basis of resistance, and two manuscripts are currently in development for publication. We have contributed to pan-genome analysis of 18 O. glaberrima accessions aimed at elucidating the structural and sequence variations linked to blast resistance, in collaboration with IRD. We have successfully established improved phenotyping techniques and facilities at Mbe for the screening of blast, RYMV, and bacterial blight. A modern greenhouse has been procured to enable speedy evaluation of breeding lines at Mbe. We have identified the most virulent strains of key rice diseases, which are used to screen promising breeding lines and released varieties for resistance prior to advancement or recommendation for use. Throughout this process, students have received training and the scope of collaboration has broadened', '2024-02-07', '- Maintain a set of differentials and relevant breeding lines\n- Evaluate breeding materials for disease resistance\n- Sources of disease resistace and associated genes/QTLs\n-  Efficient techniques for screening rice germplasm for disease resistance', 5, 'Excellent support to breeding program.', '', NULL, NULL),
(552, 'ok', '2024', 76, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 06:20:48.599', '2024-12-12 06:20:48.599', NULL, 'Leading germpalsm health unit ', 'Leading germpalsm health unit for phytosanitary certification and post-entry clearance at AfricaRice', 'I have effectively guided the GHU team in achieving these KPIs, and today GHU is acknowledged for its ability to fulfill its mandate through collaboration with NPPOs and the 10 CGIAR centers. We have improved our facilities and are committed to ongoing improvement and maintenance of the QMS standards necessary for every GHU in CGiAR. We have contributed to safe movement of seeds through development and implementation of effective phytosanitary protocols/ SOPs and diagnostic methods  more than 10000 accessions analyzed and exchanged with various partners every year', '2024-02-07', 'a)	Facilitate the exchange of genetic materials belonging to OneCGIAR across international borders, while minimising the risk of interception \nb)	Provide phytosanitary services that involve conducting diagnostics, seed treatment and field inspection of regeneration and multiplications plots to ensure the production of healthy seeds for genebank conservation and exchange\nc)	Improve knowledge on seed-borne pests and diseases in germplasm collections and exchanged seeds\nd)	Research on new seed treatment pesticides including biopesticides for preventing seed-borne pathogen transmission and optimize seed treatment techniques\ne)	Harmonization of diagnostic procedures/protocols and translating into SOPs\nf)	Strengthen biosecurity and biosafety procedures and improve seed borne pathogen bank storage efficiency\ng)	Strengthen QMS by improving other aspects such as data management, data transmission and waste disposal management/incineration\nh)	Improve pest risk assessment in instances where there exists a potential threat posed by diseases transmitted through seeds\ni)	Contribute to GHU networks for phytosanitary capacity strengthening of CG partners, NPPOs and other stakeholders\nj)	Capacity building and raise awareness about Seed health by conducting specific seminars/ workshops for staff and partner institutions on the latest diagnostic and treatment methods', 4, 'GHU is taking care of important task, the team spirit should be enanced.', '', NULL, NULL),
(553, 'ok', '2024', 76, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 07:57:00.630', '2024-12-12 07:57:00.630', NULL, 'Pathogen biology and epidemiology', 'This objective involves genetic analysis of pathogens , focusing on pathogen diversity and the evolutionary relationships among pathogen variants to understand their disease-causing potential, while quantifying their impact in various rice-producing countries. It also encompasses studying the basis of pathogenicity in order to guide breeders and plant health practitioners. In addition, we conduct epidemiological studies on rice blast and brown spot diseases, developing risk maps and validating models for informed decision making', 'We have successfully performed genome sequencing on various representative disease-causing pathogens, and now have genome data for both major and minor rice diseases available as reference genomic information to support further research and assist breeding programs and plant health practitioners. We have also successfully characterized the diversity and evolutionary relationships of significant rice disease-causing pathogens in Africa, and quantified their impact in rice-producing countries, which is crucial for informed decision-making. We carried out studies on the epidemiology of rice blast and brown spot diseases in the context of climate change, developing risk maps and validating models. Our collaboration with partners has improved, resulting in more research outputs than initially anticipated. This includes the recent optimization of genotyping by sequencing to identify the species responsible for brown spot and the development of management strategies for brown spot causing species', '2024-02-07', 'a)	Increase knowledge of pathogen genomes and pathogen diversity for better disease management\nb)	Improve knowledge of the molecular basis of pathogenicity and evolution of major rice pathogens\nc)	Research epidemiology of pathogens to provide the latest information in connection to environmental variables', 5, 'Great scientific work, it should be tailored for practical application by breeders.', '', NULL, NULL),
(555, 'ok', '2024', 123, 27, 'draft', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-12 08:18:12.069', '2024-12-12 08:18:12.069', NULL, 'Production de semence de prebase et base', 'Prparation et mise en place des parcelles de production de semences de prbase, de base des varietes amliores  dAfricaRice  et des parcelles de demonstrations pour les projets, KAFACI, TAAT II, SeedEqual\n\n', 'Disponibilit des intrants (engrais, pesticides), des matriels et outillage de production (de l\'eau d\'irrigation, des parcelles de production et de la main d\'uvre a en temps voulu', '2024-12-31', 'Emblaver 7ha pour une projection de 13 tonnes de semences', 5, 'This task was achieved achieved with outstanding quality. ', 'Production d\'un total de 13, 149 Tonnes soit :\n-	Projet SeedEqual: 3,850 Tonnes prbase (G3) de la varit ORYLUX 6 pendant la premire saison de l\'anne 2024\n-	Projet TAAT 2 : 9,280 Tonnes de semence de prbase G3 (IR841, CB1, ORYLUX6 , et CY2), et base G4 (ORYLUX6 et CY2), pendant la deuxime saison de l\'anne 2024\n', '-	Le lancement et la gestion de la production de 3 hectares de semences de la varit ORYLUX 6 pour le projet SeedEqual \n-	6 ha de semences Base (CY2, NERICA 4, ORYLUX 6) et prbase -G3 (IR841, CY2, CB1, et ORYLUX 6) ont t emblave et les activits  ont continue jusquen septembre 2024.\nUn suivi rigoureux, associ  une collaboration efficace avec les assistants et le superviseur, a assur une progression constante. Des visites de terrain rgulires ont t effectues pour garantir une gestion optimale du projet. Les difficults identifies ont t discutes lors de runions techniques, permettant de trouver des solutions appropries et efficaces.\n', 'Good progress. The production of breeder and foundation is progrssing acccording to plan'),
(556, 'ok', '2024', 76, 244, 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 08:27:52.868', '2024-12-12 08:27:52.868', NULL, 'Leading the Plant pathology unit', 'This objective involves scientific leadership of Plant pathology and germplasm health units in management of scientific outputs, planning, professional development, resource mobilization, project results and reporting among others', 'We have successfully managed our scientific outputs, achieving success in delivering project results, supervising students, and managing reporting, budgeting, and financial aspects.\n- We have engaged in various trainings, workshops, and conferences where we showcased progress in our research efforts  the list of professional development activities is lengthy. Euridice Tella had a 6 months training at PHIM Montpellier, while Marie Gouete spent 2 months at the same institution training on ELISA, sequencing and RT PCR methods. Additionally, Marie Gouete participated in a week-long training in Cameroon focused on fungal molecular identification. Raoul Agnimonhan had a one-month training on Bioinformatics and Genomics at CIBiG, facilitated by IRD, and  a two-week training focused on virus identification utilizing MinION Oxford Nanopore Technology. He also spent three days at World-Veg in Benin to receive training in VeggieMon, a tool created by the World Vegetable Center for the monitoring of pests and diseases. Aubin spent 3 months at IRD, France, training on Bioinformatics, and sequencing of O. glaberrima accessions and the analysis of genome sequencing data. Fatimata Bachabi  PDF - spent one week at CIAT participating in a GHU workshop focused on seed health and germplasm exchange\n- Contribution to resource mobilization  I am serving as the focal point for the Plant Health initiative at AfricaRice; I was also involved in Accelerated Breeding (ABI) and Genebank Initiatives; AGGRi2: Enhancing Genetic Gain and Varietal Replacement in Rice - Phase 2; Crops to End Hunger, among others; ARISE  and Diagnostics of brown spot pathogens through long-read sequencing techniques. between fricaRice CIRAD, IRD, University of Montpellier, and \n- Our efforts have also led to improvement of plant pathology laboratory and phenotyping facilities at Mbe, which include the replacement of outdated equipment and the establishment of new tools.', '2024-02-07', '- I am leading the plant pathology and GHU, which involve \n- scientific leadership\n- professional development\n- guidance of staff and appraisals \n- Planning and budgeting\n- Reporting', 5, 'Excellent leadership in capacity building and enhancing the laboratory capacity to serve its objectives. ', '', NULL, NULL),
(557, 'ok', '2024', 123, 27, 'draft', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-12 09:56:27.651', '2024-12-12 09:56:27.651', NULL, 'Purification et de maintien des varits/ lignes ', 'Purification et de maintien des varits/ lignes de amliores dAfricaRice et collecter des donnes agro morphologique pour les projets, KAFACI, SeedEqual\nMise en place des parcelles de demonstrations pour le projet KAFACI', 'Disponibilit des intrants (engrais, pesticides), des matriels et outillage de production (de l\'eau d\'irrigation, des parcelles de production et de la main d\'uvre a en temps voulu', '2024-12-31', 'Purification et de maintien d\'environ 15 nouvelles varits/ lignes amliores dAfricaRice et collecter des donnes agro morphologique ', 3, 'The activity was effectively achieved. The targeted quantities of G0/G3 were achieved.', 'Mise en place des demos de 29 varits plus trois tmoins pour le projet KAFACI. Au vu des performances, les demos de ces varits ont t reconduit dans le deuxime semestre de l\'anne. Un suivi rigoureux, associ  une collaboration efficace avec les assistants et le superviseur, a assur une progression constante. Des visites de terrain rgulires ont t effectues pour garantir une gestion optimale du projet. Les difficults identifies ont t discutes lors de runions techniques, permettant de trouver des solutions appropries et efficaces.', '- Mise en place des demos de 29 varits plus trois tmoins pour le projet KAFACI. Au vu des performances, les demos de ces varits ont t reconduit dans le deuxime semestre de lanne.\nUn suivi rigoureux, associ  une collaboration efficace avec les assistants et le superviseur, a assur une progression constante. Des visites de terrain rgulires ont t effectues pour garantir une gestion optimale du projet. Les difficults identifies ont t discutes lors de runions techniques, permettant de trouver des solutions appropries et efficaces\n', 'The demo plots for the KAFACI varieties is progressing according to plan. Twenty-nine KAFACI varieties an