(576, 'ok', '2024', 112, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 13:12:19.759', '2024-12-12 13:12:19.759', NULL, 'Regeneration of Genebank accessions ', ' produce viable and sufficient quantity of healthy and pure seeds for conservation and distribution Manage the growth of 3,188 accessions under regeneration in the field, ensuring their healthy development, and promptly report any issues or challenges encountered to the supervisor.', ' The genebank nursery area is fully prepared and ready for use.\n  The nursery supports 100% of seedlings growing healthily, with no significant issues in seedling development. \n 100% of seedlings are transplanted in strict adherence to the randomization plan, with no deviation from the experimental design', '2024-12-31', ' Break the seed dormancy according to the established protocol.\n Establish and efficiently manage the nursery to ensure healthy seedling development.\n Transplant seedlings in the field following the randomization plan with 100% compliance.\n Conduct weekly health checks for 100% of the 3,188 accessions to ensure early detection of any issues affecting growth.\n Achieve a 95% success rate in the healthy growth and regeneration of accessions, with minimal mortality or stunted growth.\n Ensure that 100% of the accessions are regularly maintained (watering, weeding, pest control) according to the established field management plan.\n Thresh, blow, weigh, and move harvested material to the drying room on the same day of harvest.', 4, 'Mr. Emmanuel demonstrated outstanding performance in managing all germinated accessions in the field, ensuring healthy plant growth and the production of viable, genetically pure seeds in sufficient quantities for conservation and distribution. Regular field monitoring was conducted, with any issues promptly reported to the supervisor. His efforts have significantly contributed to the preservation and availability of high-quality germplasm for future use.', 'All germinated accessions in the field was successfully managed, ensuring healthy plant growth and the production of viable, healthy, and genetically pure seeds in sufficient quantities for conservation and distribution. Field monitoring was conducted regularly, and any issues or challenges encountered were promptly reported to the supervisor. These efforts have contributed significantly to the preservation and availability of quality germplasm for future use.', NULL, NULL),
