(583, 'ok', '2024', 58, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 15:34:02.900', '2024-12-12 15:34:02.900', NULL, 'Awareness creation, and scaling of Smart-valleys ', 'Awareness creation, and scaling of Smart-valleys approach within the framework of the Accelerating the impact of CGIAR climate research for Africa (AICCRA-Mali), Food Security Resilience Programs (FSRP) teams and ONG partners in Niger and Mali', '', '2024-12-31', 'Number of inventoried, explored, and ranked inland valleys based on their potential for agricultural development, and development of Smart-Valleys sites in Mali,  and Niger while realizing their development plan design and development plan implementation, and training staffs and technicians from Ministry of Agriculture, NARS, and NGOs', 5, 'The staff has been excellent in strengthening staleholders capacity and establishing Smart-Valleys demonstration sites in Mali, Niger and Cote d\'Ivoire. ', '	Inventory and exploration of inland valleys to evaluate their potential for agricultural development in Mali and Niger regions.   \n	Design and establishment of development plans for inland valleys in the Regions of Sikasso and Slingu, and Dosso according to the Smart-Valleys approach in Mali and Niger, respectively.\n	Development of 7 and 3 inland valleys based on the Smart-valleys approach in Mali and Niger, respectively. \n	Training of 28 and 19 staff and technicians from Ministries of Agriculture (agricultural development agencies and programs, and research institutes), territorial administrations, and NGO partners on the adoption of Smart-valleys approach for land and water development in inland valleys in Mali and Niger, respectively.  \n	Training farmers from 10 local communities to follow up and implement the Smart-valleys approach in their inland valleys in Mali and Niger. \n	Production of the database on farmers perceptions about the performance of the Smart-Valleys appr', NULL, NULL),
