(585, 'ok', '2024', 58, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 15:50:13.662', '2024-12-12 15:50:13.662', NULL, 'Contribution to scientific papers', 'Contribution to scientific papers', '', '2024-12-31', 'All contributions to initiated, submitted, or published manuscripts such as writring, data production, data analysis, and editing.', 4, 'The staff published one paper and contributed to data collection and map production of another paper. This is commendable. ', '	Published paper: Djagba, J.F., Dossou-Yovo E.R., Sintondji, L.O., Vissin, E.W., Zwart, S.J., 2024. Assessing the Spatial Distribution Patterns of Suitable Inland Valleys for Rice Development: A Case Study for Two Contrasting Regions in Benin. Modeling Earth Systems and Environment 10, 50095025, https://doi.org/10.1007/s40808-024-02047-7.\n	Monthly climate variables (temperature maximum, temperature minimum, rainfall, and Solar radiation) collected from NASA Power to contribute to: Saito, K., Dossou-Yovo, E.R., Ibrhim, A., 2024. Ratoon rice research: Review and prospect for the tropics. Field Crops Research 314, 109414.\n	Manuscript reviewed for Applied Geomatics in Springer Nature (Publisher) in September 2024.\n	Data collected for the impact assessment of Smart-Valleys approach for land and water development and drought tolerant varieties on rice yield, nutrient use efficiency, and farmers income, and for the validation of the RIICE tool for monitoring rice area, yield, and climat', NULL, NULL),
(586, 'ok', '2024', 58, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-12 16:04:49.247', '2024-12-12 16:04:49.247', NULL, 'Identification of risks and mitigation in GIS unit', 'Contribution to identification of risks and mitigation in the GIS unit', '', '2024-12-31', 'Depending on workload', 5, 'The staff has been very effective in identifying and mitigating the risks related to the GIS activities. These include saving geospatila data on One drive and sharing access to the team members, and participating in training on upgrading skills in the use of advanced GIS softwares. ', '	Acquisition, management, and good location of all GPS data, study/experiment sites, and spatial analyses for AfricaRice staff and partners activities.\n	Successful and efficient use of GIS software and GPS for all mapping needs of AfricaRice staff by avoiding PDFs manipulation and manual data mapping.  \n	Short training of CGIAR African French-speaking partners network on efficient GPS data collection and use for their genetic resource units.', NULL, NULL),
