(594, 'ok', '2024', 227, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:38:42.059', '2024-12-13 10:38:42.059', NULL, 'Monitoring the viability of MTS and LTS', 'Compile and review all viability data from 2018 to 2023 for accessions conserved in both MTS and LTS, and submit it to the database manager for migration to the GGCE system;\n Analyze the viability data of accessions monitored in MTS and LTS, as well as the initial viability data of newly harvested seed lots\n', 'Availability of data in an Excel file or in the GGCE database', '2024-12-31', 'All viability data from 2018 to 2023 has been compiled and submitted to the data manager for migration to the GGCE system\nThe results of the viability tests conducted in 2024 for MTS and LTS, as well as for newly harvested seed lots, have been analyzed and validated in the GGCE system\n', 5, 'Tia has made significant progress in curating and transferring all viability data from 2018 to 2023 into the GRIN Global template, ensuring smooth migration to both GRIN-Global and GGCE. The analysis of viability data for 1,347 newly harvested seed lots, 5,036 LTS accessions, and 2,056 MTS accessions is thorough. Accessions with low viability are identified for regeneration in 2025, ensuring proactive management of seed health. All the data are now available in GGCE, enhancing accessibility and long-term planning for germplasm conservation. This work demonstrates strong attention to detail and effective data management.', ' All viability data from 2018 to 2023 have been curated, transferred to the GRIN Global template, and sent to the database manager for migration, first to GRIN-Global and later to GGCE\n The viability data of 1,347 newly harvested seed lots, including newly acquired germplasm, 5,036 accessions conserved in LTS and 2,056 accessions from MTS, have been analyzed. Accessions with low viability have been earmarked for regeneration in 2025. All data are available in GGCE.\n', 'All viability data from 2018 to 2023 have been curated, transferred to the GRIN-Global template, and submitted to the database manager for migration, first to GRIN-Global, and subsequently to GGCE. The data are now available in GGCE', 'Mr. Tia Dro has carried out exemplary work in the management and enhancement of viability data. He meticulously curated the data from 2018 to 2023, transferred them into the required GRIN-Global format, and submitted them to the database manager for migration. Thanks to his professionalism, all the data are now available and accessible in GGCE, thus strengthening the traceability and usability of the conserved information.'),
(595, 'ok', '2024', 41, 164, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:40:30.854', '2024-12-13 10:40:30.854', NULL, 'Installation and  reinforcement of the workshops ', 'Develop and  put in place  a  strong and  competitive workshop to support  research activities through a good maintenance program  to keep the equipment good working conditions .\nAlso develop the capability to  supervise and backstop the  outsourced maintenance  with improvement of the maintenance  quality metrics to reduce drastically the downtime .', '1- Qualified or well trained technicians \n2- Appropriate tools \n3- Spare part availability \n4- CAM (Computer assisted maintenance ) program to improve on requests management ', '2024-11-30', '1- Reduction  of downtime period for equipment and vehicles \n2- Maintain the good working conditions \n3- Reduction of the operational cost  through strong maintenance program\n4- Fabrication work (table,door ,metal construction for labs and farm)\n5- Ensure the quality control of all repair', 4, 'This need to be continued.', 'Equipment maintenance plan executed and adjusted  in a professional way \nWorshop operational to meet  the demands \nmost of the fabrication works is dvelopped  on site that helps to significantly reduced downtime period \nBeter control on the quality of repairs and maintenance ', '1- Vehicle to reinforce  maintenance plan and a mechanic engaged to reinforce the workshop capability \n2- Pro-activity  and preventive plan for maintenance to reduce significantly the heavy breakdowns \n3- Carpenter and macon contracted in house to perform some construction and fabrication works \n4- OSA updated to perform online requisition for services \n', ''),
(596, 'ok', '2024', 127, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:45:48.120', '2024-12-13 10:45:48.120', NULL, 'Regeneration of Genebank accessions ', 'Coordinate the regeneration of 3188 accessions activities to ensure that the templates for seed preparation/nurseries preparation/field preparation/ seed cleaning/seed drying/data collection are in the tablets and the traits are properly measured and recorded', '	Land for characterization is prepared and ready for use according to the planned timeline\n	All accessions received from cold rooms management team are successfully germinated\n', '2024-12-31', '	Produce at least 1,500 g of pure, healthy, and viable seeds (85% germination rate) for each accession.\n	Purify the Oryza sativa mini core collection\n	 Increase seed quantities for the Oryza sativa mini core collection, comprising 600 accessions.\n	Increase seed quantities for the Oryza glaberrima mini core collection, comprising 350 accessions\n	Increase seed quantities for the newly acquired accessions, comprising 172 accessions.\n', 3, 'I would like to highlight the need for greater attention to the work related to the regeneration of 3,188 accessions. Based on the evaluation, less than 10% of these accessions had an increased number of seeds and were actually conserved in the MTS. This indicates that future implementation of this activity must be carried out with much greater care to achieve the expected outcomes.\n\nMoving forward, it is essential to coordinate regeneration activities to ensure that all necessary templates for seed preparation, nursery preparation, field preparation, seed cleaning, seed drying, and data collection are properly integrated into the tablets. Additionally, the measurement and recording of traits must be done meticulously to maintain high-quality data.\n\nYour attention to these details will be crucial for improving the efficiency and effectiveness of this work. I appreciate your efforts and look forward to seeing better results in the next cycle.', 'Thank you very much for your encouraging words and continued support. Coordinating the agro-morphological characterization of the 1,200 conserved accessions and the 600 from the Oryza sativa mini core collection has indeed been a demanding but rewarding process.\n\nWe fully recognize the importance of ensuring data quality across all 51 traits, and we have implemented thorough validation steps to maintain accuracy and completeness. To date, 1,300 accessions have been successfully characterized, and the data is currently being cleaned in preparation for integration into GRIN-Global and Genesys.\n\nI will continue to keep you updated on our progress and will not hesitate to reach out should any challenges arise where additional support may be needed. Thank you once again for your trust and guidance.\n', 'By the end of June, a total of 1,293 accessions had been sown for seed multiplication. These efforts aim to ensure the availability of seeds for future research, safety duplication, and distribution. This includes 600 Oryza sativa accessions constituting the O. sativa minicore collection, and 350 from the Oryza glaberrima minicore collection.', 'The activities carried out over the evaluation period have contributed significantly to achieving the set objectives. Notable progress has been made in key areas, including the conservation, documentation, and availability of genetic resources. The implementation of strategic priorities, such as safety duplication, improved data management, and targeted distribution, reflects a strong alignment with long-term goals for biodiversity conservation and utilization.\n\nOne of the main strengths observed was the dedication and professionalism of the team involved. Their consistent efforts ensured timely execution of tasks, particularly in the preparation and management of core collections. Collaboration and coordination among team members and with external partners were also effective, resulting in better resource sharing and operational efficiency.'),
(597, 'ok', '2024', 127, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:45:53.762', '2024-12-13 10:45:53.762', NULL, 'Agro-morphological characterization of 1200 accs.', 'Coordinate the agro-morphological characterization of 1200 conserved accessions and, the 600 accessions of the Oryza sativa mini core collection.\nClean and validate data on 51 traits, ensuring its accuracy and completeness, and enter the finalized data into the GRIN-Global and Genesys databases\n', '	Land for characterization is prepared and ready for use according to the planned timeline\n	All 1,800 accessions are successfully germinated\n', '2024-12-31', '	Develop a comprehensive experimental protocol \n	Successfully set up experimental fields for the assessment of rice accessions.\n	Collect and clean data on 51 traits for the 1200 accessions. \n	 Collect and clean data on 51 traits for the Oryza sativa mini core collection, comprising 600 accessions.\n	Perform statistical analyses to evaluate traits and identify promising accessions for breeding programs.\n', 4, 'Great work on coordinating the agro-morphological characterization of 1,200 conserved accessions and the 600 accessions of the Oryza sativa mini core collection. This is an important step toward enhancing the value and accessibility of our germplasm collections.\n\nEnsuring the cleaning and validation of data on 51 traits is critical, and I appreciate the effort in maintaining accuracy and completeness. Entering the finalized data into GRIN-Global and Genesys will significantly strengthen our data management and make the information more accessible for global users.\n\nYour dedication to this task is commendable, and I look forward to seeing the successful completion of this objective. Please keep me updated on any challenges or support you may need.', 'Thank you very much for your encouraging words and continued support. Coordinating the agro-morphological characterization of the 1,200 conserved accessions and the 600 from the Oryza sativa mini core collection has indeed been a demanding but rewarding process.\n\nWe fully recognize the importance of ensuring data quality across all 51 traits, and we are putting in place thorough validation steps to maintain accuracy and completeness. The integration of finalized data into GRIN-Global and Genesys is well underway, and we are confident it will greatly enhance the visibility and utility of our germplasm resources.\n\nI will make sure to keep you informed of our progress and will not hesitate to reach out should any challenges arise where additional support is needed. Thank you once again for your trust and guidance.', 'A total of 1,200 accessions have been sown for agro-morphological evaluation, transplanted, and the characterization is currently ongoing.', 'Significant progress has been made in the characterization of genetic resources during this period. A total of 1,200 accessions have been successfully sown for agro-morphological evaluation, transplanted in the field, and are currently undergoing systematic characterization. This work represents a critical step in enhancing our understanding of trait diversity within the collection and contributes directly to the broader goals of conservation and use.'),
(598, 'ok', '2024', 77, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:52:05.737', '2024-12-13 10:52:05.737', NULL, 'Daily Monitoring of Cooling Equipment Functionalit', 'Monitor on the daily basis the proper functioning of cooling equipment of the MTS and LTS , in collaboration with the operations service of AfricaRice, under the coordination of the head of RBCA,', '	Temperatures and humidity levels in the two drying rooms and the storage rooms (MTS and LTS) must be maintained at the recommended levels:\n-Small Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-Large Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-Active Collection Room (MTS): +2C 3\n-Base Collection Room (LTS): -19C 3\n', '2024-12-31', '	Daily monitoring logs showing 100% compliance with checks on the cooling equipment functionality for MTS,  LTS and drying rooms.\n	Timely reporting and resolution of any equipment issues in collaboration with the operations service.\n	Consistent maintenance records confirm the proper functioning of cooling systems without significant downtime.\n', 5, 'Karlin has exhibited strong and proactive management in ensuring environmental control and operational continuity in 2024, key to the success of genebank functions.\n\nEnvironmental Monitoring:\nTemperature and relative humidity were monitored daily in all critical areas, including:\n\nSmall and Large Drying Rooms (+15C 3 and 15% 3 RH),\n\nMTS (Active Collection Room) at +2C 3,\n\nLTS (Base Collection Room) at -19C 3.\nThis consistent monitoring demonstrates Karlins strict adherence to best practices for seed conservation, ensuring seed viability and longevity.\n\nMaintenance Coordination:\nKarlin tracked and facilitated 7 interventions by the maintenance team on cool room equipment during the year, reflecting vigilance in addressing technical issues promptly and minimizing risk to the seed collections.\n\nCrisis and Contingency Management:\nWhen tiling work affected the small drying room (July 26  August 1, 2024), Karlin swiftly relocated seeds to the large drying room, ensuring that no disr', '	Daily monitoring of the temperatures and humidity  levels in the two drying rooms and storage rooms (MTS and LTS)  are monitored daily to maintain the recommended conditions:\n-	Small Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-	Large Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-	Active Collection Room (MTS): +2C 3\n-	Base Collection Room (LTS): -19C 3\n\n	For this year, 2024, 7 interventions of maintenance team on cool rooms equipment have been noted.\n\n	Tiling Work: Due to tiling work in the small drying room, seeds were transferred to the large drying room from July 26 to August 1, 2024, and they are returned to the small drying room.\n', '	Daily monitoring of the temperatures and humidity  levels in the two drying rooms and storage rooms (MTS and LTS)  are monitored daily to maintain the recommended conditions:\n-	Small Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-	Large Drying Room: +15C 3 and 15% 3 RH\n-	Active Collection Room (MTS): +2C 3\n-	Base Collection Room (LTS): -19C 3\n\n	For this year, 2024, at Mid-Term  3 interventions of maintenance team on cool rooms equipment have been noted.\n\n', ''),
(599, 'ok', '2024', 159, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:53:13.578', '2024-12-13 10:53:13.578', NULL, 'Passport and georeferenced data  for 763 ACQ', 'Enter the raw data for 763 accessions acquired between 2019 and 2024 into the GGCE system, including those obtained through collection, donation, or development by the Center. Additionally, format and organize this data according to the approved Multi-Crop Passport Descriptors (MCPD) to ensure consistent and standardized documentation of passport and georeference information for each accession.', ' Ensure that all 763 accessions have complete and accurate MCPD-compliant passport data entered into GGCE.\n Validate that the data meet quality control standards for consistency and completeness.\n Successfully transition inventory records to Conservation status by meeting criteria for germination, regeneration, and conservation steps.\n Achieve a measurable improvement in data quality reflected by the target PDCI score.', '2024-12-31', ' Achieve an average PDCI score of 6.0/10.\n Transition inventory status from Acquisition to Conservation.\n Routine monitoring: reception  regeneration  germination testing  conservation.', 5, 'Very good work throughout the year. Miss Christiane is a dedicated staff member who follows instructions carefully and listens attentively to her supervisor.\n', '100% of the 763 RBCA accessions were successfully entered into the GGCE system, meeting MCPD standards. The target PDCI score of 6.0/10 was exceeded, achieving an average score of 8.53/10. 374 Inventory statuses were transitioned to Conservation, with quality control validation ensuring data completeness and consistency.', 'I have made excellent progress, achieving MCPD-compliant data entry for 100% of the 763 acquisitions. An average PDCI score of 8.53/10, surpassing the target, reflects high data quality. Transitioning 374 inventory statuses to Conservation is commendable, showcasing adherence to monitoring protocols.', ''),
(600, 'ok', '2024', 159, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 10:58:46.147', '2024-12-13 10:58:46.147', NULL, 'Improve & update georeferenced data for 5000 acc.', 'Coordinate with the database manager in sourcing and improving the georeferenced data for 5000 RBCA accessions, focusing on completing missing entries and correcting inconsistencies. Use standardized georeferencing tools and procedures to ensure data accuracy and alignment with MCPD standards.', ' Achieve a minimum 95% completion rate for updated georeferenced data.\n Validate updates with quality assurance reviews and ensure MCPD compliance.\n Generate reports showing improvement in data completeness and accuracy.', '2024-12-31', ' Update georeferenced data for at least 95% of the 5000 accessions.\n Achieve an accuracy level of at least 90% for the updated georeference information.', 5, 'Very good work throughout the year. Miss Christiane is a dedicated staff member who follows instructions carefully and listens attentively to her supervisor.', 'Georeferenced data for 84% of the 5000 accessions were successfully updated, achieving 93% data accuracysurpassing the 90% target. Quality assurance reviews confirmed MCPD compliance, and comprehensive reports demonstrated significant improvements in data completeness.', '84% of the 5000 accessions have updated georeferenced data, nearing the 95% target. Achieving 93% accuracy surpasses expectations, and MCPD compliance has been consistently validated. Continued focus on completion will ensure the target is met.', ''),
(601, 'ok', '2024', 159, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 11:01:17.575', '2024-12-13 11:01:17.575', NULL, 'Enhancing Efficiency for 1,077 Accessions', 'Streamline the workflow for distributing RBCA accessions by implementing process improvements and automation where feasible. Ensure all distributions are accurately documented and meet delivery timelines.', ' Achieve a measurable reduction in processing time (10 days on average).\n Ensure at least 1077 accessions are successfully distributed without delays.\n Obtain positive feedback from recipients regarding the efficiency of the distribution process.', '2024-12-31', ' Distribute 1077 accessions with a reduction of average processing time from 47 days to 47 - 10 days.\n Maintain 100% adherence to documentation and distribution guidelines.', 5, 'Very good work throughout the year. Miss Christiane is a dedicated staff member who follows instructions carefully and listens attentively to her supervisor.', 'About 1410 accessions were successfully distributed, with average processing time reduced by 12 days, surpassing the target of 10 days. Documentation and distribution guidelines were adhered to 100%, and positive feedback was received from recipients, highlighting improved efficiency and satisfaction.', 'I have exceeded expectations, distributing 1500 accessions and reducing processing time by 12 days. Documentation adherence and positive recipient feedback highlight her ability to streamline workflows effectively.', ''),
(602, 'ok', '2024', 159, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-13 11:03:32.410', '2024-12-13 11:03:32.410', NULL, 'RBCA Annual Distribution and Acquisition Reporting', ' Coordinate with database manager to develop and maintain a comprehensive tracking system to document RBCA\'s yearly distribution and acquisition activities. \n  Provide timely updates and reports to ensure all activities are well-documented and accessible for stakeholders.\n Ensure users survey is sent out for each and every distributed material.', ' Deliver annual template/compilation that are complete and error-free.\n Ensure 100% traceability for all distributed and acquired accessions.\n Achieve high stakeholder satisfaction through accurate and transparent yearly user survey.', '2024-12-31', ' Produce an annual template covering 100% of distribution and acquisition activities.\n Ensure at least 95% accuracy in physical and numerical documentation.\n Follow up on users survey in collaboration with the database manager/distribution assistant.', 5, 'Very good work throughout the year. Miss Christiane is a dedicated staff member who follows instructions carefully and listens attentively to her supervisor.\n', 'Annual templates covering 100% of distribution and acquisition activities were produced and verified for 95% documentation accuracy. User surveys were sent for all distributed materials, receiving high stakeholder satisfaction rates and positive feedback. Full traceability for all accessions was ensured.', 'I have produced accurate, error-free annual templates and ensured 95% documentation accuracy. User surveys were successfully distributed, leading to high satisfaction rates. Full traceability for all accessions demonstrates her commitment to transparency.', ''),
