(621, 'ok', '2024', 112, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-16 13:18:43.191', '2024-12-16 13:18:43.191', NULL, 'Transplant and monitor at least 500 accessions', 'Transplant and monitor a minimum of 500 accessions, including both wild and cultivated types with low viability or limited grain numbers, in the screen house to regenerate the accessions, ensuring sufficient seeds are harvested, cleaned, dried, recorded, and prepared for the next planting.', ' Healthy seedlings are received form the viability testing team. \n The screen house is fully prepared and ready for use.\n Plastic pots for transplantation are prepared and ready for use.', '2024-12-31', ' Achieve a 100% transplant success rate for the 500 pregerminated accessions, ensuring proper establishment in the screen house.\n  Ensure 100% of the accessions (including those with low viability or limited grain) regenerate successfully, producing viable seeds for future planting.\n  Ensure 100% accuracy in recording all relevant data (e.g., seed quantity, accession status) for each of the 500 accessions. ', 4, 'Mr. Emmanuel effectively carried out regeneration activities in the screen house, resulting in the production of sufficient seeds. All harvested seeds were properly cleaned, dried, documented, and prepared for the next planting cycle. His efforts have contributed to the recovery and conservation of valuable genetic resources.', ' Regeneration activities in the screen house were effectively carried out, resulting in the production of sufficient seeds. All harvested seeds were properly cleaned, dried, documented, and prepared for the next planting cycle. This effort has contributed to the recovery and conservation of valuable genetic resources.', NULL, NULL),
(622, 'ok', '2024', 112, 217, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-16 14:03:24.696', '2024-12-16 14:03:24.696', NULL, 'Assist in Oryza glaberrima panicles collection', 'Provide support in the collection of Oryza glaberrima panicles for phenotyping, ensuring proper handling, labeling, and documentation of samples for detailed analysis of panicle traits.', ' The agronomy team establishes the fields within the planned timeline. \n Plastic folders are prepared, labeled, and available according to the field plan.', '2024-12-31', ' Prepare plastic folders labeled according to the randomization plan for panicle collection. \n Collaborate closely with the agronomy unit team to collect mature panicles promptly. \n Ensure that 100% of collected panicles are sent to the post-harvest laboratory for scanning on the same day.', 4, 'Mr. Emmanuel provided effective support in the collection of Oryza glaberrima panicles for phenotyping. All samples were properly handled, accurately labeled, and thoroughly documented, ensuring high-quality data collection for detailed analysis of panicle traits. His contribution has strengthened the reliability and precision of the phenotyping process.', 'Support was effectively provided in the collection of Oryza glaberrima panicles for phenotyping. All samples were properly handled, accurately labeled, and thoroughly documented, ensuring high-quality data collection for detailed analysis of panicle traits. This contribution has supported the reliability and precision of the phenotyping process.', NULL, NULL),
