(631, 'ok', '2024', 218, 41, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-16 15:37:56.551', '2024-12-16 15:37:56.551', NULL, 'Irrigation des parcelles', 'Irriguer les parcelles au profit des chercheurs\n', '1- Bon tat du circuit d\'irigation (canaux, drain, vannes, diguettes, tuyauterie) ;     \n2- Bon tat d fonctionnement de la motopompe ;                                                     \n3-Une disponibilit en carburant ;                                                                                \n4- Une disponibilit de la main d\'oeuvre.  ', '2024-12-31', 'Faire l`irrigation conformment au calendrier d`irrigation tabli dans le protocole de recherche comme suit :                                                 \n1-Respect des bonnes priodes d\'irrigation ;                                        \n2-Respecter la profondeur d\'humidit recommane ;                             \n3-Respecter les frequences d\'apport d\'eau aux cultures.', 3, 'Travail satisfaisant et correctement apprecie des demandeurs ', 'l irrigation a ete faite selon les periodes d irrigation et aussi les frequnces d apport d eau aux cultures.', '', 'Se deroule bien selon le programme etabi'),
(632, 'ok', '2024', 218, 41, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2024-12-16 15:39:48.252', '2024-12-16 15:39:48.252', NULL, 'Support de recherche', 'Mettre en place des supports de soutien  la recherche au prifit des chercheurs\n', '1- Disponibiliser des informations relatives  l`essai ;                                                          2-Octroyer le budget  pour la ralisation de la pancarte ;                                                                                      3- Disponibiliser les intrants agricoles  temps (engrais, sememces) ;                                                                  4-Disponibiliser la main d\'oeuvre ;                                                                                    \n5- Bon tat des quipements agricoles ;                                                                           6- Disponibiliser le carburant.', '2024-12-31', '1-30 pancartes ont t confectionnes et fixes au bord des chaque ssai et comportant les informations y relatives ;                                      \n 2- 4 demonstrations ont t conduites avec 8 varits de riz de plateau et 6 varits de bas-fond afin de metre en exergue les resultats de la recherche ;                                                                               3-Installation de deux station mto pour l\'accompagnment de la recherche.', 3, 'Bien fait et satsfaisant dans l\'ensembe ', 'Tous les pancarts ont ete confectionnes et installes.\nles parcelles de demonstrations ont ete mis en place\nles differentes stations meteo ont ete installees', '', 'Se deroule en lien avec les besoins et les protocoles etablis '),
(633, 'ok', '2024', 127, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-17 09:02:23.171', '2024-12-17 09:02:23.171', NULL, 'Oryza panicles architecture assessment ', 'Collaborate with the agronomy unit team to perform panicle phenotyping using an advanced imaging system, ensuring accurate and high-throughput data collection for detailed trait analysis', '	Land for Oryza glaberrima evaluation is prepared and ready for use according to the planned timeline\n	Agronomy team establish the fields according to the planned timeline\n', '2024-12-31', '	Collect 5 panicles per accessions and per repetition from at least 200 accessions in both the MB and Korhogo fields\n	Scan each panicle and extract structural data, including the number of grains, primary branches, and secondary branches using P-TRAP program\n	Perform statical analysis and identify promising Oryza glaberrima accessions for breeding.\n', 5, 'Collaborating with the agronomy unit to leverage advanced imaging for panicle phenotyping will greatly enhance data accuracy and efficiency. High-throughput analysis will provide valuable insights for trait characterization.', 'Were excited about the collaboration with the agronomy unit and the potential of advanced imaging technologies to enhance panicle phenotyping. The shift toward high-throughput analysis is already contributing to improved data accuracy and deeper insights into key traits. So far, panicles from 120 Oryza glaberrima accessions have been successfully phenotyped at two sites: Mb and Korhogo.', 'The fields have been set up in Mb and Korhogo, and data collection is ongoing in accordance with the established protocol.', 'The fields have been successfully set up in both Mb and Korhogo, marking a major milestone in the implementation of the agro-morphological evaluation activities. The team has ensured that all preparatory stepsfrom land preparation to transplantingwere carried out efficiently and in alignment with the project timeline.\n\nData collection is currently ongoing in accordance with the established protocol, reflecting a strong commitment to maintaining scientific rigor and consistency across locations. The dedication and coordination demonstrated by the field teams are commendable, especially given the logistical challenges involved in managing multiple sites.'),
(634, 'ok', '2024', 127, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', 'sent', '2024-12-17 09:02:25.583', '2024-12-17 09:02:25.583', NULL, 'Automate seed characterization', 'Characterize at least 5000 accessions conserved accession seed using Multispectral Image System (MSI) and draft scientific paper on rice descriptor development using Multispectral Image System (MSI)', '	Accessions are received form from cold rooms management team according to the planned timeline successfully', '2024-12-31', 'Scan at least 25 seeds per accession using the Videometer\n	Clean BLOBs (multi-spectral images) for each accession and extract data on 300 traits including developed descriptors \n	Perform statical analysis and identify promising accessions for breeding\n', 5, 'Characterizing 5,000 accessions with MSI will significantly enhance seed trait analysis, ensuring precision and efficiency. The scientific paper on rice descriptor development will be a valuable contribution to the field.', 'Over 6,000 accessions have been characterized using multispectral imaging (MSI), and a scientific manuscript has been prepared for publication.', 'By the end of June, 5,763 accessions had been characterized using the Videometer. This extensive characterization effort significantly contributes to our comprehensive understanding of the accessions. Additionally, a manuscript has been drafted and submitted for internal review.', 'Good work. Mr kpeki did a great work by characterizing seed of conserved accessions using the videometer. A research paper was written and it is under reviewed. '),
(636, 'ok', '2024', 77, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-17 09:10:32.888', '2024-12-17 09:10:32.888', NULL, 'Monitoring water activity data in the seeds.', 'Ensure that the data related to the moisture content of the seeds of accessions in the drying rooms are stored in the database.', 'The GGCE database must be fully operational to enable data storage. \nAnd the connectivity must be available\n', '2024-12-31', '	Data Accuracy and Completeness: Percentage of error-free entries and proportion of accessions with recorded moisture content data in the database.', 5, 'Karlin efficiently processed 1,856 accessions by cleaning, drying, packing, and accurately positioning them in the MTS room. He ensured that moisture content data for each accession was properly recorded in the GGCE database. This reflects her strong commitment to quality control and data integrity in seed management.', '	A total of 1856 accessions cleaned, dried, packed and positioned in MTS room are their moisture content in database (GGCE).', '	Approximately 930 accessions were cleaned, dried, packed, and positioned in the Medium-Term Storage (MTS) room, with their corresponding moisture content data recorded in the GGCE database.\n	About 170 accessions were similarly processed and positioned in the Long-Term Storage (LTS) room, with moisture content information also entered in the GGCE database.\n\n', ''),
(637, 'ok', '2024', 59, 151, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2024-12-17 09:16:07.373', '2024-12-17 09:16:07.373', NULL, 'Maintain field and characterization laboratory equ', 'Ensure all field and characterization laboratory equipment, including tablets, cales, grain counters, sprayers, hoes, machetes, and sickles, are regularly maintained and in optimal working condition to support efficient and accurate research activities', '	All equipment is inspected and serviced on schedule, with no equipment failures due to lack of maintenance.\n	All required equipment is available and operational when needed for research activities, minimizing delays.\n	All measurement equipment is properly calibrated before use, ensuring accurate and reliable data collection for research.\n', '2024-12-31', '	Ensure that 100% of field and laboratory equipment is inspected and serviced at least once per quarter to maintain optimal functionality.\n	Achieve 100% equipment availability, ensuring all necessary tools (tablets, scales, grain counters, sprayers, hoes, machetes, and sickles) are ready for use during scheduled activities.\n	Maintain a 100% or higher functionality rate for all field and laboratory equipment, with minimal downtime for repairs.\n	Ensure that 100% of equipment repairs or replacements are completed within 48 hours of identification of issues.\n	Calibrate and validate 100% of measurement equipment (scales, grain counters) before each use to ensure accurate data collection.\n', 5, 'Ange Dossou Yovo ensured all equipment was available, inspected, and fully operational for research activities, with any delays or missing label information promptly addressed. Additionally, all measurement equipment was properly calibrated before use, guaranteeing accurate and reliable data collection.', 'All equipment were available, inspected, and operational for research activities and any delays or missing information on labels was notified.  \nAll measurement equipment was properly calibrat