(814, 'sent', '2024', 272, 149, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-01-13 14:10:01.399', '2025-01-13 14:10:01.399', NULL, 'Provide technical assistance and scale climate-sma', 'By April 2025, provide technical assistance and scale climate-smart technologies by profiling AfricaRice innovations and technologies, developing and assessing innovation packages for scalability. Collaborate with the TAAT Rice Compact team to finalize and submit annual work plans and budgets by designated deadlines. Facilitate the procurement of goods and services for TAAT-supported initiatives, contribute to resource mobilization efforts, and proactively identify and mitigate risks associated with assigned duties, ensuring alignment with the Center\'s objectives. ', 'Donor approval of the annual workplans and budget', '2024-12-31', '- Climate smart technologies profiled\n- Annual workplans and budgets developed\n- Procurement plan developed\n- Contribution to resource mobilization ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(815, 'sent', '2024', 272, 149, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-01-13 14:10:08.330', '2025-01-13 14:10:08.330', NULL, 'Establish and facilitate functional MSIPs', 'By April 2025, establish and facilitate functional Multi-Stakeholder Innovation Platforms (MSIPs) across TAAT II and TSF countries to enhance rice sector development hubs. Mobilize key rice value chain actors, including millers, processors, aggregators, input dealers, SMEs, machinery fabricators, financial institutions, researchers, and policymakers, to scale rice technologies and innovations. Collaborate with Africa-wide Rice Task Forces (TFs) to develop the competence of MSIP actors in adopting advanced technologies and innovations. Additionally, contribute to the creation and dissemination of extension materials, videos, rural radio programs, and success stories promoting quality agricultural inputs. ', 'Functional MSIPs and Task forces in each country.', '2024-12-31', '- Number of functional MSIPs facilitated in each country\n- List of key value chain actors mobilized \n-  List of capacity trainings done to develop MSIPs competences\n- List of extension materials developed and disseminated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(816, 'sent', '2024', 272, 149, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-01-13 14:10:11.270', '2025-01-13 14:10:11.270', NULL, 'Promote agribusiness models ', 'By April 2025, promote agribusiness models focused on entrepreneurship for youth and women in collaboration with ENABLE-TAAT Compacts. Organize regional and field-level training sessions, learning visits, workshops, and conferences on seed production and Good Agricultural Practices (GAPs) in partnership with FARA, IWMI, IFDC, and other stakeholders. Additionally, establish agribusiness linkages within the rice value chain to strengthen agri-input-related enterprises. \n', 'Functional women and youth groups and working collaborations with the mentioned partners', '2024-12-31', '- Developed business models focussed on women and youth\n- Organized regional field level trainings on seed production and GAPs\n- Agribusiness linkages established within the rice value chain to promote agri-input related enterprises.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
