(949, 'ok', '2024', 273, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-27 09:31:37.664', '2025-03-27 09:31:37.664', NULL, 'Irrigation impact analysis', 'Analyze different irrigation treatments to determine their influence on crop yield, biomass produced, water productivity, economic profit.\n', '-Quality of database\n-Availability of resource persons to provode additional information\n-Access to  any other relevant source of information\n', '2024-12-31', '-Relevance of analysis results for decision making\n-On-time delivery of the draft of the results\n', 4, 'The staff has been able to simulate the effects of irrigation on the agronomic performance of vegetables produced in off-season in lowland systems. Although the results need to be fine-tuned, the preliminary estimates show good technical skills of the staff. ', 'Thanks to this objective, I have gained in-depth knowledge of how irrigation affects the yield or productivity of water.', 'The Irrigation impact analysis objective is progressing well, with the analysis remaining aligned with its objective of supporting water use efficiency and profitability optimization strategies. The next steps are to finalize the writing of the article and prepare it for submission.', ''),
(950, 'ok', '2024', 273, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-27 09:49:27.892', '2025-03-27 09:49:27.892', NULL, 'Optimization to Maximize Yield and Income', 'Identify optimal irrigation strategies (frequency and dose) that simultaneously improve economic profitability and water use efficiency. \nTo achieve this, a multi-objective optimization approach is implemented via the NSGA-II (Non-dominated Sorting Genetic Algorithm II) algorithm, which explores trade-offs between:\n\n-Yield maximization (t/ha),\n-Minimizing water quantities (m/ha),\n-minimizing depletion costs ($/ha).\n\nThe solutions generated (Pareto front) will enable farmers to choose strategies adapted to their local constraints, and policy-makers to promote practices that balance competitiveness and climate resilience.', '--Quality of database; \n-Efficient integration and parameterization of NSGA-II to solve the problem.\n-Availability of resource persons to provode additional information\n-Access to  any other relevant source of information\n', '2024-12-31', '-Relevance of analysis results for decision making\n-On-time delivery of the draft of the results\n', 4, 'The staff has tried an optimization approach of irrigation water use to maximize water productivity and yield. Although the results are not yet confirmed, this trial demonstrated the capacity of the  staff to learn quikcly and develop skills in otpimization modeling. ', 'Thanks to this objective, I understand the optimization issues and my work will enable me to propose optimization strategies, such as balancing water supply and crop income potential.', 'The \"Optimization to maximize yield and income\" objective is progressing as planned, focusing on identifying optimal irrigation strategies that balance economic profitability and water-use efficiency. The next steps are to finalize the writing of the article and prepare it for submission.', ''),
(952, 'ok', '2024', 273, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-27 10:54:47.439', '2025-03-27 10:54:47.439', NULL, 'Yield prediction with ML using Aquacrop output', 'The objective is to determine which machine learning algorithms can accurately predict crop yields under different irrigation treatments, using a minimal set of input data. As the AquaCrop crop growth model requires a large number of input variables, we will exploit its results as a database for training and evaluating machine learning algorithms. This will enable the development of efficient yield prediction models, even when the availability of field data is limited.', '-Data access.\n-Knowledge of the AquaCrop model and its use to simulate irrigation scenarios.\n-Knowledge of Machine Learning algorithms.\n-Programming skills (Python) and use of ML libraries (e.g. scikit-learn).\n', '2024-12-31', '-Number of AquaCrop output variables important for yield prediction;\n-Number of algorithms evalueted;\n-Ranking of the best algorithms for yield prediction based on evaluation metrics.\n-On-time delivery of the draft of the results', 4, 'The candidate tool the initiative to use machine learning to simulate rice and vegetable yields using the outputs of the Aquacrop model. Being able to produce those results in a short period of time is commendable. ', 'Thanks to this objective, I\'ve gained in-depth knowledge of data processing and can use AquaCrop results in a machine learning model. ', 'The study remains aligned with its goal of creating accurate yield prediction tools that require minimal input data, while taking advantage of AquaCrop\'s comprehensive simulation capabilities. The study has moved from mid-term to final completion, with all objectives met and results documented in a research paper that is currently being finalized and will then be shared with my supervisor and will soon be ready for publication.', ''),
