(987, 'ok', '2024', 7, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-28 10:31:54.912', '2025-03-28 10:31:54.912', NULL, 'EES sustainability performance assessment', 'Evaluate the economic, environmental and social (EES ) sustainability performance of rice cultivation in the project intervention areas\n', 'Engagement of the stakeholders\nResources\' availability\n', '2024-12-31', 'Number and nature of related tasks achieved', 5, 'The staff provided strong support in the protocol design and data collection and analysis and well as in the drafting of the reports by the interns. All the interns successfully defended their thesis and received their degree, which is very much commendable.  ', 'CIS and CSA technologies being disseminated in the framework of AICCRA project in Mali aim to sustainably enhance the performance of rice-based systems in project areas through the promotion of practices that contribute to biodiversity and improve some performance indicators including nutrient use efficiency, water and labor productivity, yield, grain quality, food security and farmer incomes. These CSA performances are being evaluated through 21 study topics. The interns are being assisted to finalize their dissertation and )if applicable manuscript writing.', 'CIS and CSA technologies being disseminated in the framework of AICCRA project in Mali aim to sustainably enhance the performance of rice-based systems in project areas through the promotion of practices that contribute to biodiversity and improve some performance indicators including nutrient use efficiency, water and labor productivity, yield, grain quality, food security and farmer incomes. These CSA performances are being evaluated through 21 study topics. Interns have been selected and are now being assisted to draft manuscript from the data collected from the framework of their graduation.', ''),
(988, 'ok', '2024', 7, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-28 10:32:02.528', '2025-03-28 10:32:02.528', NULL, 'Strengthening the capacity of extensionists ', 'Strengthen the capacity of public and private sector extension workers, and farmers for the adoption of climate-smart water systems, nutrient management, nature-based solutions, and climate-smart rice varieties by hundreds of thousands of farmers.\n', 'Enablers and willingness of multi-stakeholders for the adoption of the technologies\nResource for the implementation of the activities', '2024-12-31', 'Number of training sessions for public and private sector extension workers, and farmers for the adoption of CSA technologies\nNumber of supporting actions conducted\n', 4, 'The staff led the training sessions related to the environmental and safeguard assessments and ensured they are enforced by the partners and beneficiaries. The current environmental and safeguard mission from the World Bank has been successful, partly due to the valuable contribution of the staff. ', 'In Mali, a refresh session has been carried out on the environmental and social standards of the World Bank. Moreover, mechanical weeders and transplanters including 225 units of each are purchased to support farmer productivity. \n', 'In Mali, thousands stakeholders including farmers and public and private actors over the project intervention sites are constantly receiving training and technical supports on diverse CIS and CSA technologies. As part of the additional funding, 12 additional sites have been screened to extend the project area to reach further beneficiaries. This leads to updating the ESMP and disclosing a related notice through Essor-Mali, a Mali newspaper. Likewise, mechanical weeders and transplanters including 225 units of each are being purchased to support farmer productivity. \nAs incentive strategy for large-scale adoption of integrated rice-fish systems :\n-	in Mali, 02 additional demonstration sites including 01 led by women cooperative have been developed in Selingue. 08 farmers are being supported in Sirakoro, Rassogoma, Goursy, Kossouka, Nago Sahel, Togou, Dioro and Temou \n-	In Ivory Coast, 06 farmers organization leaders in Bouake and 03 in Gagnoa are trained by AfricaRice', ''),
(989, 'ok', '2024', 7, 60, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-28 10:35:30.368', '2025-03-28 10:35:30.368', NULL, 'CSA promotion activities ', 'Undertake climate-smart storage and processing technologies promotion actions, including dissemination, identification of potential adoption barriers and incentive mechanisms and assessment of impact on farmers particularly women and youth.', 'Engagement of the stakeholders\nResources\' availability', '2024-12-31', 'Number of stakeholders\' consultation sessions organized \nNumber of demo sites established \nNumber of survey conducted to identify the barriers to adoption', 4, 'The staff has been very much supportive in faciliating the activities related to the post-harvest innovation assessment and their scaling in Mali. Preliminary results were quite postive and need to be strengthened. ', '2 stakeholder consultations were organized prior to the World Bank E&S evaluation. These activities targeted 197 and 124 (including 60% women) key informants from the different project sites.\nThe lessons learnt for these consultations are many. For example, a paddy parboiling workshop in Dioro, is a women-led cooperative of 165 members operating mainly at the processing stage of rice value chain. Before the project intervention, the cooperative was using traditional parboilers. The cooperative is being supported by AICCRA-Mali with a GEM parboiler and many others capacity building activities. The consultation session pointed that GEM parboiler improved their productivity, product quality and benefit and reduced their parboiling time and cost', 'In addition to the 16 new demonstration sites selected as part of the scaling activities, 2 consultation activities have been carried out to assess the impacts of the project interventions on the communities. These activities targeted 197 (including 58% women) and 124 (including 60% women) key informants from the different project sites. This also highlighted the barriers and incentives to 