(1002, 'sent', '2024', 276, 60, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-03-28 11:01:02.650', '2025-03-28 11:01:02.650', NULL, 'Reports on the adoption and impact ', '-Analyzed data on four different studies on the adoption and impact of CSA and CIS innovations on the welfare of rice farmers\n-Developed four reports on the adoption and impact of CSA and CIS practices and innovation on farmers welfare\n', '-Improved welfare indicators (rice yield, income per hectare, food and nutritional security), for adopters of CSA and CIS practices and technologies \n-Improved income, women\'s dietary diversity, child dietary diversity, and used and access rights for women\n-Developed four reports on the adoption and impact of different CSA and CIS practices and technologies: 1) Adoption and Impact of Climate Information Services Dissemination Platform on Farmers Yield, Income and Food Security in Mali, 2) Adoption and Impact of Drought-Tolerant Varieties, RiceAdvice app, Mechanization, and Climate Information Services on Welfare Indicators of Farmers in Mali, 3) Adoption and Impact of Crop Diversification in Rice-Based Systems on Farmers income, yield, and food security in Mali, 4) Impact of GEM parboiling technique on womens income and food security in Mali\n', '2024-12-31', '-Preliminary analysis of the impact of adoption on welfare indicators\n-Women empowerment\n-Final report \n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1003, 'sent', '2024', 211, 48, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-03-28 12:17:56.896', '2025-03-28 12:17:56.896', NULL, '1. Global Initiatives / CGIAR Portfolio: ', 'Key Achievements', '	CGIAR-Genetic Innovation: Established the AfricaRice Breeding Research Services Hub for West and Central Africa (WCA) to support high-throughput genotyping and EBS services across all crop breeding programs.\n	CGIAR-Global Rice Breeding Platform: Developed a structured framework for the international exchange of elite germplasm and personnel among AfricaRice, IRRI, and CIAT.\n	BIOFLOW Implementation: Positioned AfricaRice as an early adopter of CGIARs digital innovation, BIOFLOW, integrating it into all breeding programs and extending its application to 10 key NARES partners.\n	CGIAR-CAPSHA: Facilitated the nomination, selection, and placement of NARES scientists in African and Asian institutions through the CGIAR-CAPSHA program in collaboration with IITA.\n	CGIAR-BMGF-PPP Initiative: Successfully submitted competitive concept notes to BMGF, with one selectedout of all CGIAR centersby a high-level BMGF and CGIAR panel for full proposal development.\n	CGIAR-Breeding for Tomorrow Science Program: Contributed as a Writing Team member, dedicating 68 months to developing the full science program in collaboration with CGIAR colleagues.\n', '2024-12-31', 'Key Achievements in 2024', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1004, 'ok', '2024', 172, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-28 12:32:08.682', '2025-03-28 12:32:08.682', NULL, '1. Optimizing AfricaRice Irrigated Breeding', '	Optimized breeding scheme- to deliver higher genetic gain with cost-effective, increased speed & higher accuracy.\n	Implement Population improvement by increasing frequency of desirable alleles.\n	Achieving increased heritability of all trails (On-station & On-farm) specific to the breeding pipeline(s) with improved crop management practices, frequent contacts & better communication with stake holders.\n', 'using RGA technique and recycle parent in stage ', '2024-12-31', 'To deliver increased genetic gain.', 4, 'Excellent effort to catch up with the modernization breeding protocol.', 'This year 2024 has been a very good start for me as an irrigated lowland rice breeder. I fully understand all the terminology of modern rice breeding program', 'Optimized breeding and testing scheme- to deliver higher genetic gain with cost-effective, increased speed & higher accuracy.\nImplementation of Modern Parental Selection Strategy / Reconstitution of Crossing block', ''),
(1005, 'ok', '2024', 172, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'sent', '2025-03-28 12:34:35.705', '2025-03-28 12:34:35.705', NULL, '2.	Product Evaluation ', '	Establishing Stage 1, MET, OFT, NPT trails  With defined testing networks and SOPs.\n	Data collection, Data management, Combined analysis & Data-driven decisions with EBS unit of AfricaRice.\n	Sampling and Coordination for grain quality tests, HT genotyping, disease & pests screening.\n', 'on station testing, MET, on farm testing ', '2024-12-31', 'Testing, Trailing and Data-driven decisions', 4, 'Accomplished the trialing according to the new breeding protocols.', 'in 2024 I successfully conduct all irrigated trials, LST stage1, Stage 2 Stage 3 has been conducted based on the protocols. Also, I contribute with NARES to conducted  on-farm and NPT', 'phenotype and genotype stage 1 trial,  implement multi-location field trials across various countries  for stage 3, under diverse environmental conditions. ', ''),
