(1034, 'sent', '2024', 211, 48, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-03-30 13:18:06.163', '2025-03-30 13:18:06.163', NULL, 'AfricaRice GDI & Breeding Portfolio: Key Achieveme', 'AfricaRice GDI & Breeding Portfolio: Key Achievements in 2024', 'AfricaRice GDI & Breeding Portfolio: Key Achievements in 2024\nRedefined and Optimized AfricaRice Breeding Programs: To deliver increased genetic gain.\n	Refined global breeding programs, aligning them with market segments through defined TPPs, germplasm development, and strategic product evaluation and deployment.\n	Implemented a modern parental selection strategy and restructured the crossing block.\n	Optimized breeding schemes to enhance genetic gain, improve cost efficiency, accelerate delivery, and increase accuracy.\n	Advanced population improvement by increasing the frequency of desirable alleles.\n	Enhanced heritability across all trials (on-station & on-farm) by improving crop management practices, strengthening engagement with NARES, and fostering better communication with stakeholders.\n	Progressed towards full integration and optimization of speed breeding, RCGS, and data-driven decision-making.\nProduct Evaluation: Testing, Trials, and Data-Driven Decision- AfricaRice Breeding Pipelines\n	Trial Implementation: Established Stage 1, MET, OFT, and NPT trials with standardized testing networks and SOPs.\n	Data Management & Analysis: Conducted data collection, management, and combined analysis in collaboration with the AfricaRice EBS unit to drive informed decision-making.\n	Quality & Trait Assessments: Coordinated sampling for grain quality testing, high-throughput genotyping, and disease & pest screening.\nKey Achievements in 2024:\n	Market-Driven Breeding: Transitioned from ecology-based breeding to market segment-linked breeding pipelines at AfricaRice.\n	Breeder-NARES Engagement: Established continuous monitoring and interactions between AfricaRice breeders and NARES during trialing seasons.\n	Strategic Partnerships: Executed and implemented LoAs and MoUs with 15 NARES countries.\n	Elite Germplasm Sharing: Distributed over 3,000 elite breeding lines to 15 NARES countries for testing and variety release.\n	Extensive Trialing Network: Conducted 86 trials (Stage 1, MET, OFT, NPT) across 15+ NARES countries.\n	Genetic Gain Assessment: Reported annual genetic gain estimates for each breeding program to CGIAR, ABI, and BMGF for the first time.\n	Expanded MoU Agreements: Signed over 12 new MoUs with strategic partners.\n	Regular Program Reviews: Organized monthly GDI review and planning meetings.\n	Leadership Reporting: Presented GDI progress and plans to AfricaRice leadership, BoT, Council of Ministers, and Program Committee.\n	CGIAR Project Reporting: Provided updates on CGIAR Genetic Innovation Initiatives (ABI & AGGRi 2) to PRMS.\n	Impact Assessment Contributions: Supported BMGF studies on varietal replacement and potential transformative products in Africa.\n	Future Funding Initiatives: Developed and presented \"Concept Notes\" to BMGF for upcoming funding opportunities.\n	Advisory & Mentorship: Provided guidance to GDI units, including Plant Health, Gene Bank, Bioinformatics, CtEH-Mechanization, Molecular Breeding, and Germplasm Development.\n	Cross-Disciplinary Integration: Fully incorporated Plant Health, Grain Quality, Gene Bank, Entomology, EBS, BIOFLOW, and HT Genotyping into AfricaRice breeding programs.\n	Strategic Leadership: Led AfricaRice-GDI to global recognition, ensuring alignment with CGIAR, BMGF, industry, and key stakeholders.\n\n', '2024-12-31', 'Key Achievements in 2024', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
