(1099, 'ok', '2024', 151, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 18:16:27.398', '2025-04-19 18:16:27.398', NULL, 'Coordinate genebank operations and ensure that the', 'This objective focuses on the effective management and enhancement of genebank operations to ensure that the collection of genetic resources is preserved, documented, and made accessible in alignment with international best practices. It encompasses four core pillars: availability, safety duplication, data and information management, and distribution.\n\nThe aim is to ensure that the genebank\'s germplasm collection is viable, secure, well-documented, and readily available to users including researchers, breeders, and national agricultural programs. It also includes enhancing operational efficiency', 'Effective coordination among field, laboratory, and data management teams to align activities with operational timelines.', '2024-12-31', 'Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)\nAvailability\n\nAt least 90% of accessions of the collection are viable and available for distribution upon request.\n\nSafety Duplication\n\n90% of the collection duplicated in a second secure location (e.g., Svalbard, ori Fort Collins).\n\nData and Information Management mainly the Passeport Data Completeness Index (PDCI) >7\n\nFull integration and real-time updates within the genebank information system (e.g., GGCE or GRIN-Global CE).\n\nDistribution\n\nAnnual increase in the number of distributed accessions and recipient countries/institutions.\n\n\n', 5, 'Grear coordination and achievement.', 'In 2024, I played a pivotal role in advancing the operations and research of the Rice Biodiversity Center for Africa (RBCA). Under my leadership, the genebank exceeded key performance indicators in seed availability (91%), safety duplication (93%), and passport data completeness. I coordinated overall operations to ensure sustained progress in viability testing (5,454 accessions) and targeted regeneration. Over 1,410 accessions were efficiently distributed through our improved request platform. I also led the enhancement of accession data qualitymolecular, passport, and phenotypicusing tools like the Videometer and GGCE. Our visibility on Genesys was expanded, supported by regular audits and staff training. I ensured robust Quality Management System (QMS) implementation across eight core elements, including updated SOPs and risk mitigation plans. Innovations in seed viability and regeneration, especially for O. glaberrima, boosted success rates. ', NULL, ''),
(1100, 'ok', '2024', 151, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 18:27:59.117', '2025-04-19 18:27:59.117', NULL, 'Improve the Efficiency of At Least Two Genebank Op', 'This objective aims to optimize core genebank functions by improving the efficiency of at least two operational components, such as seed viability testing, regeneration,  seed characterization, Enhancing operational efficiency not only reduces turnaround time and resource waste but also ensures better service delivery to users', 'Monitoring and evaluation mechanisms in place to track improvement and compliance', '2024-12-31', 'Two or more genebank operations improved (e.g., reduced processing time, increased throughput, automation of workflows)', 4, 'The work is expected to increase the efficiency of the Genebank, but to what extent the efficiency is increased it it not clear.', 'Under my leadership, the AfricaRice Genebank made major strides in modernization and sustainability in 2024. I successfully led the proposal and procurement process for acquiring solar panels, marking a key step toward a \"Green Genebank.\" I coordinated with internal units to ensure transparency and timely supplier selection. I also oversaw infrastructure maintenance, resolving logistical and procedural challenges. I spearheaded the full migration to GRIN-Global Community Edition (GGCE), securing data through VPS integration and enhancing operational efficiency. Integration with Genesys improved global visibility. I led continuous staff training to align with new systems. These achievements reflect strong leadership in driving innovation and resilience.', NULL, NULL),
(1101, 'ok', '2024', 151, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 19:33:18.804', '2025-04-19 19:33:18.804', NULL, 'Organize and supervise the genebank  review', 'This objective focuses on strengthening the strategic, operational, and scientific dimensions of the genebank by successfully organizing and overseeing a comprehensive external review. This includes coordinating with reviewers, compiling documentation, and ensuring timely delivery of review materials. The objective also includes developing and submitting a robust Business Continuity Plan as part of the requirements for the long-term grant, ensuring the genebank\'s resilience and operational sustainability.\n\nIn addition, the objective entails the timely and quality submission of at least two project reports, two new project proposals, and two scientific publications', 'Timely coordination with external reviewers, donors, partners, and internal teams.\n\nAccess to updated and accurate data and documentation to support review and reporting.', '2024-12-31', 'Successful coordination and completion of the genebank external review with submission of final report and recommendations.\n\nBusiness Continuity Plan finalized and submitted to the donor or relevant authority by the agreed deadline.\n\nTwo high-quality project reports submitted on time, meeting all donor requirements.\n\nTwo competitive project proposals developed and submitted to potential funders.\n\nTwo peer-reviewed publications submitted to reputable scientific journals.', 5, 'Excellent achievement.', 'Under my leadership, the AfricaRice Genebank achieved outstanding results in 2024. I successfully organized and led the External Review process, preparing all required reports, manuals, and staff briefings, which earned praise from the review panel for excellence in leadership and staff performance. I authored the business continuity plan, led the writing of two project proposals, and coordinated two publications. My grant writing secured new funding from the Rural Development Administration of South Korea and helped maintain the $1M+ annual support from the Genebank Initiative. I also ensured the Genebank met performance targets, qualifying for Long-Term Funding from the Crop Trust. Additionally, I co-convened the writing of the 20252030 Genebank proposal, aligning it with key CGIAR initiatives.', NULL, NULL),
(1102, 'ok', '2024', 151, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 19:47:15.268', '2025-04-19 19:47:15.268', NULL, 'Strengthen capacity of NARS and students on geneba', 'This objective aims to enhance the technical capacity and operational knowledge of National Agricultural Research Systems (NARS) partners and students in genebank management. It involves designing and delivering targeted training programs, workshops, and hands-on learning opportunities in areas such as seed regeneration, characterization, documentation, safety duplication, and data management. Through mentorship and knowledge-sharing, the objective supports the development of a new generation of professionals who can contribute to the sustainable management and utilization of plant genetic resources in their respective countries and institutions.\nBy fostering regional expertise and improving local capacities, this objective contributes to long-term sustainability, promotes the use of best practices aligned with international standards', 'Strong collaboration and coordination with NARS partners and academic institutions.', '2024-12-31', 'At least 1 training session or capacity-building workshops conducted during the year.\n\nMinimum of 10 participants trained, including NARS staff and university students', 5, 'Great committment in Capacity Sharing with NARES.', 'Under my leadership, the AfricaRice Genebank has become a vital regional asset, driving innovation in rice research and training. I facilitated regional training for NARS staff, supported seed restoration efforts in Liberia and Nigeria, and coordinated collaborations with national genebanks in Benin and Kenya. I led the organization of the successful CGIAR Genebank Initiative training in Nairobi, enhancing the technical knowledge of 16 NARS participants. Additionally, I initiated strategic partnerships with CGIAR centers (ILRI, CIAT, IITA) to improve genebank operations and database management. These efforts have significantly strengthened our regional impact and capacity for collaboration.', NULL, NULL),
(1103, 'ok', '2024', 151, 244, 'sent', 'sent', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 20:14:06.559', '2025-04-19 20:14:06.559', NULL, 'Coordinate molecular activities and represent RBCA', 'This objective focuses on ensuring strategic leadership and coordination of molecular biology activities within the Rice Biodiversity Center for Africa (RBCA), particularly those linked to genotyping, molecular characterization, and quality control of rice germplasm. It also includes representation and active engagement in CGIAR-wide initiatives, working groups, and strategic planning sessions related to the Genebank Initiative.\n\nThe objective aims to promote alignment with global standards, foster collaboration across CGIAR centers, and raise the visibility of RBCAs research contributions. It ensures that AfricaRices molecular efforts are effectively integrated into broader initiatives such as genomics-assisted conservation and breeding, contributing to the effective use and long-term security of rice genetic resources.', 'Active participation and recognition within CGIAR Genebank Initiative and related forums.', '2024-12-31', 'At least 2 subsets of accessions developed based on molecular characterization  activities \n\nParticipation in at least 4 CGIAR Genebank Initiative meeting', 5, 'Great coordination and visibility of AfricaRice Genebank in the CGIAR community. ', 'Under my leadership, the AfricaRice Genebank has advanced rice genetic research, developing 158 SNP markers for quality control and genotyping 5,289 accessions. The creation of the O. sativa Core Collection, with 600 accessions, captures 95% of genetic diversity, supporting global food security. In 2024, new subsets (5) were developed, focusing on traits like flooding tolerance, anaerobic germination, salinity resistance, and enhanced zinc concentration, addressing environmental and nutritional challenges. Molecular characterization of 9,013 accessions revealed significant genetic diversity, while a pangenomic study led to the creation of the improved rice pan-genome CG14v3, boosting breeding efforts and biodiversity conservation.', NULL, NULL),
(1104, 'ok', '2025', 151, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 20:48:27.265', '2025-04-19 20:48:27.265', NULL, 'Coordinate Genebank Operations to Exceed KPIs ', 'This objective focuses on the comprehensive coordination and oversight of genebank operations to ensure that the management of the rice genetic resources collection meets and surpasses international standards. The aim is to strengthen the overall efficiency and reliability of the genebank\'s core functions, including the availability of accessions for distribution, securing safety duplicates, maintaining accurate and up-to-date passport and characterization data, implementing  quality management systems (QMS), and fulfilling germplasm requests effectively.', 'Reliable funding and operational budget to support critical activities such as regeneration, seed health testing, packaging, and shipment.', '2025-12-31', '>90% availability of accessions of the collection for international distribution.\n\n 90% safety duplication of the collection at two internationally recognized sites (e.g., Svalbard and a CGIAR partner).\n\nMost of the accessions of the collection with complete and verified passport and characterization data in the database.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1105, 'ok', '2025', 151, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 21:21:12.268', '2025-04-19 21:21:12.268', NULL, 'Improve the efficiency of at least two genebank op', 'This objective aims to increase the operational efficiency of the genebank by modernizing workflows and/or introducing cost- or time-saving technologies. The focus is on identifying and targeting two specific operational areassuch as seed processing, viability testing, data entry, regeneration, inventory management, or germplasm distributionfor measurable improvement.\nEfficiency gains may include reducing human labor, time per task, input costs, or procedural redundancies while maintaining or improving output quality. The adoption of digital tools, automation, revised protocols, or advanced equipment will be used as strategic levers to optimize performance.', 'Training and capacity building provided to genebank staff to ensure successful adoption and use of new tools or procedures', '2025-12-31', 'Documented implementation of at least two new or improved workflows/technologies ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1106, 'ok', '2025', 151, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 21:32:50.651', '2025-04-19 21:32:50.651', NULL, 'Write and submit Business Plan for the Long-Grant', 'This objective focuses on fulfilling key strategic, reporting, and scientific deliverables that support the genebanks long-term sustainability, visibility, and impact. It involves preparing and submitting a comprehensive Business Plan as required under the Long-Term Partnership Agreement (LTPA), including forward-looking financial and operational strategies. It also entails developing high-quality reports and budget justifications for two ongoing projects, ensuring timely compliance with donor and institutional expectations.\nAdditionally, this objective includes the development of one concept note to seek new funding opportunities and support innovation in genebank operations or research. Lastly, by contributing to two peer-reviewed articles.', 'Clear internal deadlines and responsibilities assigned for drafting and reviewing all deliverables.\nClose coordination with finance, communications, and scientific teams to gather accurate data for reports and budgets.\n', '2025-12-31', 'One Business Plan submitted and approved.\nTwo complete and timely project reports and budgets submitted \nOne concept note submitted for funding or collaboration by December 2025.\nContribution to two peer-reviewed scientific publications', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1107, 'ok', '2025', 151, 244, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-19 21:40:38.929', '2025-04-19 21:40:38.929', NULL, 'Lead Area of Work 5 (AoW5) activities of the CGIAR', 'This objective focuses on providing strategic and operational leadership for Area of Work 5 (AoW5) within the Genebank Accelerator. AoW5 strengthening partnership and capacity building\nAs the lead, the role involves coordinating with multiple CGIAR and partner genebanks to define common priorities, develop and align a comprehensive workplan and budget, and establish a Theory of Change (ToC) that clearly articulates pathways to outcomes, performance metrics, and expected impacts. This includes convening partners, overseeing activities, and reporting on progress to ensure AoW5 effectively contributes to the goals of the overall Genebank Accelerator.\n', '	Effective engagement and communication with CGIAR partners.\n	Clear understanding of Genebank Accelerator goals and investment priorities, ensuring AoW5 contributes meaningfully to its overall vision\n', '2025-12-31', '	One comprehensive AoW5 workplan developed and submitted \n	Budget for AoW5 activities finalized \n	Theory of Change (ToC) for AoW5 drafted, reviewed by partners, and formally approved.\n	Regular coordination and engagement with at least 5 genebanks\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1108, 'sent', '2025', 244, 277, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-21 08:17:34.057', '2025-04-21 08:17:34.057', NULL, 'Data driven decision making', 'Testing, Trailing and Data-driven decisions of sub-tropical breeding pipeline by Establishing Stage 1, MET, OFT, NPT trails  With defined testing networks and SOPs.\n	Data collection, Data management, Combined analysis & Data-driven decisions with EBS unit of AfricaRice.\n	Sampling and Coordination for grain quality tests, high through-put genotyping, disease & pests screening.\n', 'Data precision, and high heritablility for yield components and biometrician', '2025-12-30', 'Lines with high breeding value are selected', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1109, 'sent', '2025', 244, 277, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-21 08:17:35.485', '2025-04-21 08:17:35.485', NULL, 'Capacity sharing', 'Atleast ONE  training session conducted per year\nResearch publications at least 1-2 and  Project reports submitted\n\nCapacity Building Events (Short- & Medium-Term Trainings)- \nNew publication in 2024\nAssessment of the seed system in East and South African project focus countries\nDevelop National Seed Road Map with partners in the seed value chain. \n', 'Effective linkage with NARES and seed system of the project focus countries.', '2025-12-30', 'Partners are equipped with modern breeding concept and high quality seed production and delivery tools', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(1110, 'sent', '2025', 244, 277, 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', 'draft', '2025-04-21 08:28:58.195', '2025-04-21 08:28:58.195', NULL, 'Generate transformative products', '2-3 varieties released through sub-tropical breeding pipeline\nBig on-farm demonstrations, and linkage with private sector to take up the varieties and continue the seed production.\nQuality early generation seed production (nucleus and breeder seeds) and linkage with seed scaling & seed systems research.\n', 'Clear market driven product selection and registration pathway. Well coorinated seed  platform for seed prodcuciton and distribution', '2025-12-30', 'Release varieties with high impact to bring transformation in the livelihood of the producers and address the market preferences.\nQuality seed availability for the released varieties.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
